    skos:prefLabel "Account ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA565> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA563> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA565" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Activity ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA570> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA563> ;
    skos:definition "A generalized ABE and specializations that provide capacity and capacity demand for products, services, and resources. Capacity is the ability to provide some capability. For example, one measure of network capacity is the ability of a network to provide a certain amount of bandwidth during the month of May.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA570" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Capacity ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA573> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA563> ;
    skos:definition "A Configuration (also referred to as a Profile) defines how a Resource, Service, or Product operates or functions in terms of Characteristic Specifications and related Product/Service/Resource Specifications as well as Characteristics and related Product/Service/Resource entities. A Configuration may contain one or more parts (which is realized by using the Atomic/Composite pattern, but it is represented as a single entity - ConfigurationRelationship), and each part may contain zero or more fields. Each field may have attributes that are statically or dynamically defined. Some of these fields have fixed values, while others provide values from which a choice or choices can be made (e.g., using the EntitySpec/Entity and/or CharacteristicSpec/CharacteristicValue patterns).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA573" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Configuration and Profiling ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA574> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA563> ;
    skos:definition "Goal ABE represents a set of information that captures the definition of a goal or target for a process (task/activity/workflow/etc.) to reach or achieve. <br/><br/>Goals trigger and guide behavior help to guide focus and enable sustain momentum. Goals are needed to give direction, identify what's important, measure progress towards success, foster motivation, assure accountability, and assert control. <br/><br/>There is a distinction between Goal and Metric. This ABE is intended to reflect that distinction, as well as address the need for both. While a GOAL captures information about a target, a METRIC provides the yardstick or unit of measuring such achievement. Goal and Metric work hand-in-hand and each can be managed and modeled independently to bring flexibility to automation. The importance of this ABE is to capture the essence of dynamic goal setup and updates, which is key to enabler higher levels of goals management and goals management automation.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA574" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Goal ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA575> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA563> ;
    skos:definition "The Intent ABE contains the entities needed for specifying basic attributes and relationships that describe an Intent.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA575" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Intent ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA582> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA563> ;
    skos:definition "The Segmentation ABE contains all entities used for specifying rules to divide a large set of Entities instances into subsets according to criteria. These subsets are called segments.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA582" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Segmentation ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA583> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA563> ;
    skos:definition "A test is a procedure intended to establish the quality, performance, or reliability of an entity, especially before it is taken into widespread use. A test may also be executed upon the entity after it is in use to diagnose problems related to the correct functioning of the entity. As such, a test may be executed against a product, a service, or a resource.<br/> The tests are divided into three categories: <br/>• Pro-active/Controlled. Tests that are established during the fulfillment process on an entity, and are generally run continuously throughout the lifetime of the entity. These tests are often used to establish correct functioning of the entity under test before providing the entity to a consumer. The results of these tests may be queried at any given time. <br/>• On-demand/Controlled. Tests that are requested at a specific point in time, but that may also be scheduled to actually execute at a future point in time. These tests are normally run as part of assurance processes; they are used to either detect problems, or to guarantee quality, performance, or reliability commitments made to the consumer of the function provided by the entity under test. These tests are controlled in the sense that they are “managed” and can be suspended, resumed, and for which results may be requested. <br/>• On-demand/Uncontrolled. Tests that are requested to execute immediately, and for which the request is blocking until the test completes and returns results in real time. These tests are uncontrolled in that they may not be “managed”. Test ABE is specialised for Product Test ABE, Service Test ABE and Resource Test ABE.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA583" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Test ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA584> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA563> ;
    skos:definition "Graphs are a generalized (mathematical) model for defining topologies in terms of logical entities called Vertices and the relationships between them called Edges [ ref Topological graph theory - Wikipedia ]<br/><br/>For the Communications Industry, two practical specializations of graphs are commonly used:<br/><br/>Adjacency Graph - A Graph expressing an adjacency requirement or property, independently of how this is realized (which would be expressed using a Connectivity Graph).<br/>Adjacenc” is defined as the ability for a set of entities to communicate [TR 244 ]<br/>Connectivity Graph -A Graph expressing the realization of adjacency [TR 244 ]<br/>Knowledge Graph. As OSS and BSS start to incorporate AI, Knowledge graphs are created for capturing the relationships between customers’ products, services, and resources including network. Knowledge Graphs can be modelled as a specialization of mathematical graph but with a broader set of relationship types than is typical in network topology graphs.<br/>References:<br/><br/>Further description and examples of network topology graphs are available in <br/><br/>TR255A Connectivity Patterns for Virtualization Management v4.0.1 | TM Forum<br/><br/>TR244 TM Forum Information Framework Enhancements to Support ZOOM R15.0.1 | TM Forum<br/><br/>These are explained further after the introduction to mathematical graphs.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA584" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Topology ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA585> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA563> ;
    skos:definition "A description of a problem that can be shared between the service provider and the customer. Trouble or Problem is an indication that an entity (such as Resource, Service or Product) is no longer functioning according to the expected SLA.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA585" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Trouble or Problem ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA586> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA563> ;
    skos:definition "Represents a record used for reporting and managing the resolution of Trouble or Problem. This ABE is not fully developed.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA586" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Trouble Ticket ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA588> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA563> ;
    skos:definition "Workflow is a business process model, or a generic process model that is made up of series of business processes or activities that collectively through them a piece of work passes from initiation to completion.<br/><br/>A workflow ties business processes or activities together in sequence to enable realize specified objectives.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA588" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Workflow ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA589> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA603> ;
    skos:definition "Enables pricing to be based on a combination of CharacteristicSpecifcations and their related CharacteristicSpecValues.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA589" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Characteristic Pricing ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA592> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA578> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA592" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Performance Specification ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA593> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA578> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA593" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Performance Threshold ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA594> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA590> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA594" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Performance Category Specification ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA595> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA627> ;
    skos:definition "The Metric Collection ABE is initialized but has to be further studied during iteration 3.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA595" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Metric Collection ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA596> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA627> ;
    skos:definition "The Metric Job ABE contains entities corresponding to the differnt type of measurement jobs for Metric.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA596" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Metric Job ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA598> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA579> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA598" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Policy Framework ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA599> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA579> ;
    skos:definition "The Policy Specification ABE contains entities that define the invariant characteristics and behavior of policy entities. This enables multiple instances to be derived from a single specification entity. In this derivation, each instance will use the invariant characteristics and behavior defined in its associated template.<br/><br/>This domain includes specifications for a PolicyRule, its components, and how multiple PolicyRules can be grouped together.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA599" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Policy Framework Spec ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA600> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA579> ;
    skos:definition "The Policy Management ABE contains entities that are used to manage other entities in other Domains. This includes entities from other Common Business Entities sub-domains (e.g., Location and Party) as well as other sibling Domains (e.g., Product, Service and Resource).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA600" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Policy Management ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA602> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA581> ;
    skos:definition "A pattern that enables associations to be dynamically created between explicitly modeled SID entities (classes and subclasses) as well as implicit subclasses created using the EntitySpecification/Entity pattern.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA602" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Association ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA604> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA581> ;
    skos:definition "A collection of entities that can be used to dynamicall specify various identification formats for any type of entity and to represent identification instances associated with entities.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA604" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Entity Identification ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA605> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA581> ;
    skos:definition "A collection of entities that can be used to define related entity specification actions and workflows.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA605" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Entity Specification Action ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA606> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA581> ;
    skos:definition "A collection of entities that can be used to define external system capabilities like fulfillment, charging, assurance, policy and billing.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA606" ;
    skos:prefLabel "External System Capability ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA607> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA581> ;
    skos:definition "The Root Entity Group ABE enables groups of Root Entities to be related as an alternate to using the RootEntityRelationship entity in order to reduce the number of instances of RootEntityRelationship. It also enables choices of Root Entities to be made from the group. For example, choose 3 out of 7 channel packs. And, to define expressions that constrain Root Entity members of a group. For example, either channel pack 3 or channel pack 4 can be chosen, but not both.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA607" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Root Entity Group ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA608> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA591> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA608" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Performance Collection ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA609> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA591> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA609" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Performance Production ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA610> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA625> ;
    skos:definition "The Metric Definition Measure Threshold ABE contains all entities describing the threshold used for MetricDefMeasure.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA610" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Metric Definition Measure Threshold ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA611> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA601> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA611" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Policy Action ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA612> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA601> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA612" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Policy Condition ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA613> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA601> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA613" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Policy Event ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA1_EA5_EA614> a skos:Concept ;
