<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA14_EA5780> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA14_EA5770> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA14_EA5780" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Usage Example Instances"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5830> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "The Criterion is the definition of information classifying an Entity from the model (represented by an instance of RootEntityType).<br/>A Criterion classifies only one RootEntityType, i.e. it helps grouping instances of only one Entity of the SID model.<br/>Examples:<br/><ul><li>the Criterion “Age” classifies Party (instance “Party” of RootEntityType)</li><li>the Criterion “Installation city” classifies Resource</li></ul>A Criterion might be<br/><ul><li>either an existing information related to an Entity</li></ul> • in this case we need to specify where the information can be found <br/> • the Attribute carrying the Criterion information (RootEntityTypeCharSpec)<br/> • the Entity carrying the Criterion’s Attribute<br/> • and the Relationship between the Entity classified by the Criterion and the Entity where the Criterion can be found (AssociationSpecification)<br/><ul><li>or an information that has to be calculated</li></ul> • in this case we need a rule that specifies when it has to be calculated and how to calculate the information (cf. CriterionCalculationRule)<br/> • the calculated information might be recorded or not. <br/> • If not, it is only used to evaluate the condition for the Criterion. <br/> • If yes, we need to specify where it has to be recorded <br/> • the Attribute carrying the Criterion information (RootEntityTypeCharUse)<br/> • the Entity carrying the Criterion Attribute (RootEntityType)<br/> • and the Relationship between the Entity concerned by the Criterion and the Entity where the Criterion is recorded (AssociationSpecification)<br/><i>Note:</i><br/><ul><li><i>Only attributes carried by an Entity directly related to the Entity concerned by the Criterion can be specified to record the Criterion’s value.</i></li><li><i>As many relationships might exist between the Entity classified and the Entity carrying the Criterion attribute, we may need to specify which type of relationship is concerned (AssociationSpecification)</i></li></ul>For more information about RootEntity / RootEntityType pattern, refer to the Common guide book.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5830" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Sgt.01 - Criterion overview"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5832> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "Three types of Criterion exist.<br/><ul><li>Case 1: <b>Existing information</b></li></ul><ul><li><ul><li>The information corresponding to some criteria previously exist in the model. In this case, we only need to specify where the information is.</li><li>Here the country of residence of a Party can be found thanks to the relationship “is citizen of” between Party and Country in the attribute “iso3code”</li></ul></li><br/></ul><ul><li><ul><li></li><li></li></ul></li><br/></ul><ul><li>Case 2: <b>Calculated information not recorded</b></li></ul><ul><li><ul><li>The information corresponding to some other criteria do not exist directly in the model and have to be calculated.</li><li>In this case, the first option is to calculate it each time it is required and not to record it.</li><li>Here “age” and “is a customer” are calculated for each use.</li></ul></li><br/></ul><ul><li><ul><li></li><li></li></ul></li><br/></ul><ul><li>Case 3: <b>Calculated Information recorded</b></li></ul><ul><li><ul><li>The second option is to calculate it each time an event occurs (Ex: each first day of the month) and to record it in the model.</li><li>In this case, we specify where the information is recorded to use this when we use the criterion.</li></ul></li><br/></ul><br/>Here Mobile voice and Fixe Internet usage per month are calculated and recorded in the Entity PartyScore.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5832" ;
    skos:prefLabel "[Sgt-01-I01] Examples of Criteria"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5834> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "“Country of residence”, “Age” and “Is a Customer” are Criteria classifying Parties.<br/><ul><li>The “Country of Residence” is found in the attribute iso3code of the Country entity related to the Party through the relationship “is citizen of”</li><li>The “Age” is the result of a calculation based on the birth date of the Party</li><li>The “Is a Customer” is calculated checking if the Party plays a Customer PartyRole or not.</li></ul>But “Country of installation” is a Criterion used to classify Resources.<br/><ul><li>The “Country of Installation” is found in the attribute iso3code of the Country entity related to the Resource through the relationship “is installed at”</li></ul><p/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5834" ;
    skos:prefLabel "[Sgt-01-I02] Examples of Entities classified"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5836> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "A SegmentationSpecification specifies rules (CriterionCondition) to divide a large set of Entity’s instances into subsets according to criteria. These subsets are called segments.<br/>Segmentation might be defined so that segments might be disjoined or not, continuous or discontinuous.<br/>For example, Market segmentation divides a broad target market into subsets of consumers, businesses, or countries that have, or are perceived to have, common needs, interests, and priorities, and then designing and implementing strategies to target them.<br/>We mainly consider Parties’ segmentation, but we could also segment other concepts such as Resources, Projects…<br/>For example, we could define rules to identify Resources that have a high level of risk of failure.<br/>The SegmentationSpecification is evaluated to produce the corresponding Segmentation according to a triggering event. It might be “one shot”, a periodicity or at any update of criteria.<br/>The SegmentSpecification attributes lowerSize and upperSize specify the targeted limits for the size of the calculated Segment.<br/>A Segmentation might be decomposed as Segments each of them being a combination of Conditions (combined with AND or OR). These Segments are specified thanks to the SegmentSpecification.<br/>A SegmentSpecification is described by Criteria that all concern the same RootEntityType.<br/>For example, a market segmentation may contain several segmentations Pan European, Sub-Saharan Africa…, each of them being decomposed as combined conditions (Ex: Pan European Segmentation decomposed as Mobile reluctant, Basic Communicators, Pragmatics…segments)<br/>A CriterionCondition specifies a condition expressed using Criteria and might be Atomic or Composite.<br/>Each AtomicCriterionCondition specifies a condition on a Criterion such as “If Age #gt; 36”.<br/>Each CompositeCriterionCondition combines two or more AtomicCriterionConditions specifying if all the AtomicCriterionConditions must be True (AND) or if at least one of them must be True (OR).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5836" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Sgt.02 - Segmentation and Segment Specifications"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5838> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "The Pan European Segmentation is divided into 6 Segments<br/><ul><li>Mobile reluctant</li><li>Basic Communicators</li><li>Pragmatics</li><li>Mobile centric Digital Adults</li><li>Digital Adults</li><li>Digital Tribes</li></ul><p/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5838" ;
    skos:prefLabel "[Sgt-02-I01] Pan European Segmentation"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5840> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "The Pargmatics segment is composed of Parties with the following criteria<br/><ul><li>Over 36 years old</li><li>between 1 and 2 hours of Mobile usage</li><li>between 10Go and 100Go of Internet usage</li><li>living in Europe</li><li>is an Orange Customer</li></ul><p/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5840" ;
    skos:prefLabel "[Sgt-02-I02] Pragmatics Segment"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5842> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "According to the SegmentionSpecification or SegmentSpecification triggeringEvent, the Segment is built.<br/>The validity period is calculated according to the triggering event.<br/>For example, the Pan European Segmentation’s calculation might be triggered each month, therefore a Pragmatics Segment will be calculated in January classifying Parties P1, P2 and P3 and another one will be calculated in February classifying Parties P1, P2 and P4. It is assumed that in February, the Party P3 do no longer comply with the Pragmatics Segment’ CriterionCondition and that party P4 complies with it.<br/>The Segment classifies RootEntity’s instances for which the CriterionCondition is “True” when it is built.<br/>The attribute respectsThreshold specifies if the Segment respects the lower and upper size defined by the SegmentSpecification.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5842" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Sgt.03 - Calculated Segment"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5844> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "A Segmentation might be decomposed as Segments each of them being a combination of Conditions (combined with AND or OR). These Segments are specified thanks to the SegmentSpecification.<br/>Segmentation might be defined so that segments might be disjoined or not, continuous or discontinuous.<br/>For example, the market segmentation contains several segmentations Pan European, Sub-Saharan Africa…, each of them being decomposed as combined conditions (Ex: Pan European Segmentation decomposed as Mobile reluctant, Basic Communicators, Pragmatics…segments).<br/>The size of the calculated Segment corresponding to a SegmentationSpecification might be limited by a lower and upper size.<br/>A SegmentSpecification might be composite. In this case, each SegmentSpecification composed refine the criteria specified at the CompositeSegmentSpecification level.<br/>A CompositeSegment corresponds to the sum of the composed Segments.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5844" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Sgt.04 - Sub-Segments"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5846> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "A PartyProfileSpec is a type of SegmentSpecification to specify rules for classifying Parties.<br/>A PartyProfile is a type of Segment that classifies Party’s instances for which the CriterionCondition is “True” when it is built.<br/>A PartyProfile is the result of applying a PartyProfileType when a triggeringEvent occurs.<br/>The validity period is calculated according to the triggering event.<br/>A DemographicSegment is a type of PartyProfile where corresponding rules are based on feature or quality of the Party such as age, income, education, revenue, and so forth.<br/>A MarketSegment is a type of PartyProfile that groups Parties. MarketSegments are the target of MarketingCampaigns, ProductOfferingSpecifications, product promotions, product placements, and product programs from both internal and external (Competitors, and other Suppliers) perspective.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5846" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Sgt.05 - Party Segments"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5849> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5849" ;
    skos:prefLabel "[Sgt-01-I01]"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5850> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5850" ;
    skos:prefLabel "[Sgt-01-I02]"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5851> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5851" ;
    skos:prefLabel "[Sgt-02-I01]"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5852> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5852" ;
    skos:prefLabel "[Sgt-02-I02]"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5853> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "Each AtomicCriterionCondition specifies a condition on a Criterion such as “If Age #gt; 36”.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5853" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AtomicCriterionCondition"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5854> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "An AtomicSegment is a type of Segment that doesn’t have any subordinate Segment.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5854" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AtomicSegment"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5855> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "An AtomicSegmentSpecification is a type of SegmentSpecification that doesn’t have any subordinate SegmentSpecification.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5855" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AtomicSegmentSpecification"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5856> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "Each CompositeCriterionCondition combines two or more AtomicCriterionConditions specifying if all the AtomicCriterionConditions must be True (AND) or if at least one of them must be True (OR).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5856" ;
    skos:prefLabel "CompositeCriterionCondition"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5857> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "A CompositeSegment is a type of Segment composed of Segments (composite or atomic).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5857" ;
    skos:prefLabel "CompositeSegment"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5858> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "A CompositeSegmentSpecification is a type of SegmentSpecification composed of SegmentSpecifications (composite or atomic).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5858" ;
    skos:prefLabel "CompositeSegmentSpecification"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5859> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "The Criterion is the definition of information classifying an Entity from the model (represented by an instance of RootEntityType).<br/><br/>A Criterion classifies only one RootEntityType, i.e. it helps grouping instances of only one Entity of the Orange SID model.<br/><br/>Examples:<br/><br/> • the Criterion “Age” classifies a Party (instance “Party” of RootEntityType)<br/><br/> • the Criterion “Installation city” classifies an InstalledResource<br/><br/>A Criterion might be<br/><br/> • either existing information related to an Entity<br/><br/> • in this case we need to specify where the information can be found <br/><br/> • the Attribute carrying the Criterion information (RootEntityTypeCharSpec)<br/><br/> • the Entity carrying the Criterion’s Attribute<br/><br/> • and the Relationship between the Entity classified by the Criterion and the Entity where the Criterion can be found (RelationshipType)<br/><br/> • or information that has to be calculated<br/><br/> • in this case we need a rule that specifies when it has to be calculated and how to calculate the information (cf. CriterionCalculationRule)<br/><br/> • the calculated information might be recorded or not. <br/><br/> • If not, it is only used to evaluate the condition for the Criterion. <br/><br/> • If yes, we need to specify where it has to be recorded<br/><br/> • the Attribute carrying the Criterion information<br/><br/> • the Entity carrying the Criterion Attribute<br/><br/> • and the Relationship between the Entity concerned by the Criterion and the Entity where the Criterion is recorded<br/><br/>Note: <br/><br/> • Only attributes carried by an Entity directly related to the Entity concerned by the Criterion can be specified to record the Criterion’s value.<br/><br/> • As many relationships might exist between the Entity classified and the Entity carrying the Criterion attribute, we may need to specify which type of relationship is concerned (RelationshipType)<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5859" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Criterion"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5860> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "A CriterionCalculationRule is a type of PolicyRule used to specify how to calculate the value of a Criterion.<br/><br/>The rule is evaluated when an event occurs. If the condition clause is satisfied, then the pass-action clause will be executed; otherwise, the fail-action clause will be executed.<br/><br/>In a CriterionCalculationRule, the action corresponds to the Criterion’s calculation and if needed the record of it.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5860" ;
    skos:prefLabel "CriterionCalculationRule"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5861> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "A CriterionCondition specifies a condition expressed using Criteria.<br/><br/>A CriterionCondition might be Atomic or Composite.<br/><br/>Each AtomicCriterionCondition specifies a condition on a Criterion such as “If Age #gt; 36”.<br/><br/>Each CompositeCriterionCondition combines two or more AtomicCriterionConditions specifying if all the AtomicCriterionConditions must be True (AND) or if at least one of them must be True (OR).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5861" ;
    skos:prefLabel "CriterionCondition"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5862> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "A Segment is the result of applying a SegmentSpecification when a triggeringEvent occurs.<br/><br/>The validity period is calculated according to the triggering event.<br/><br/>The Segment classifies RootEntity’s instances for which the CriterionCondition is “True” when it is built.<br/><br/>The attribute respectsThreshold specifies if the Segment respects the lower and upper size defined by the SegmentSpecification.<br/><br/>A Segment might be composite. A CompositeSegment corresponds to the sum of the composed Segments.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5862" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Segment"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5863> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "A SegmentationSpecification specifies rules (CriterionCondition) to divide a large set of Entity’s instances into subsets according to criteria. These subsets are called segments.<br/><br/>For example, Market segmentation divides a broad target market into subsets of consumers, businesses, or countries that have, or are perceived to have, common needs, interests, and priorities, and then designing and implementing strategies to target them.<br/><br/>We mainly consider Parties’ segmentation, but we could also segment other concepts such as InstalledResources, Projects…<br/><br/>For example, we could define rules to identify InstalledResources that have a high level of risk of failure.<br/><br/>The SegmentationSpec is evaluated to produce the corresponding Segmentation according to a triggering event. It might be “one shot”, a periodicity or at any update of criteria.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5863" ;
    skos:prefLabel "SegmentationSpecification"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5864> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5848> ;
    skos:definition "A Segmentation might be decomposed as Segments each of them being a combination of Conditions (combined with AND or OR). These Segments are specified thanks to the SegmentSpecification.<br/><br/>Segmentation might be defined so that segments might be disjoined or not, continuous or discontinuous.<br/><br/>For example, the market segmentation of Orange contains several segmentations Pan European, Sub-Saharan Africa…, each of them being decomposed as combined conditions (Ex: Pan European Segmentation decomposed as Mobile reluctant, Basic Communicators, Pragmatics…segments).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA15_EA5864" ;
    skos:prefLabel "SegmentSpecification"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5901> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are business entities aggregated under the <b>Anomaly Entity </b>Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5901" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure AnE.01 - Anomaly Entity ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5905> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Represents the category/classification of an Anomaly - for example Infrastructure, Network Overlay/Underlay, Service Provisioning etc. Each AnomalyCategory will have set of characteristics values specified based on CharacteristicSpecification that can be used for additional attributes / constraints<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5905" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyCategory"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5906> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Subclass of CharateristicValue. A value of a characteristic provided for AnomalyCategory that further defines what the AnomalyCategory represents<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5906" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyCategoryCharacteristicValue"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5907> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Subclass of CharacteristicValue. Represents the characteristics of the Anomaly defined using AnomalyCharacteristicsSpecification<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5907" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyCharacteristicValue"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5908> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Specific action to be initiated for the Indicator once the qualifying condition is met<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5908" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyConsequence"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5909> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Abstract class that represents the runtime context (operational reality) of Anomaly. AnomalyContext carries the intermediate management view of Anomaly depending on the particular stage of the Anomaly management such as Prediction, Detection, Mitigation etc. There can be specific AnomalyContexts for each stage of Anomaly management and are typically immutable.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5909" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyContext"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5910> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Values: true,falseDefault: False"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5910" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyDetectionContext"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5911> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Represents the grouping of the Anomaly based on a particular need. For example, if the Anomaly need to be grouped based on a set of network nodes in a network topology or particular infrastructure deployment (rack/slot). AnomalyGrouping defines additional criteria for grouping the Anomaly management logic rather than limiting to individual entities. The grouping criteria are defined using AnomlayGroupingSpecification.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5911" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyGrouping"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5912> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Subclass of CharacteristicValue. A value of a characteristic provided for AnomalyGrouping that further defines what the AnomalyGrouping represents<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5912" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyGroupingCharacteristicValue"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5913> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Represents specific aspects such as metrics that is measured for determining the Anomaly on an entity. These measurements are fed into the AI/ML models to classify if it qualifies to be an Anomaly or not. A set of thresholds, applicability (such as time period, tolerance levels etc) can be used to guide the classification of the anomaly. The Anomaly Indicator characteristics are represented using AnomalyIndicatorSpecification. AnomalyIndicator is associated with an AnomalyConsequence to represent the suggested administrative action, however the action may be decided by an Anomaly Closed Loop depending on the embedded AI/ML logic. There can be different consequences depending on the AnomalyIndicator threshold levels and a notification (Alarm or Event) is initiated to notify monitoring Anomaly Closed Loop on the measurement.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5913" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyIndicator"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5914> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Values: true,falseDefault: False"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5914" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyMitigationContext"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5915> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Represents the event notifications associated with a particular indicator belonging to Anomaly<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5915" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyNotification"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5916> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Values: true,falseDefault: False"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5916" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyPredictionContext"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5917> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Represents the Anomaly status report being sent periodically or based on specific events such as state change . Derived from the BusinessInteraction (from Business Intraction ABE)<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5917" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyReport"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5918> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "A rule that defines the condition (raise or clear) to achieve to apply consequences when a threshold (AnomalyThresholdSet) is crossed or ceased to be crossed. It also defines the severity of the raise or clear of the threshold.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5918" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyThresholdRule"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5919> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "A threshold for an AnomalyIndicator used as a guiding value for initiating the Anomaly Management process<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5919" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AnomalyThresholdSet"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5920> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Concrete class inherited from Anomaly abstract class that represents an Anomaly associated with the Product domain. For example the Anomaly in Product Offer uptake, Anomaly in Product Order orchestration (such as fallout)<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5920" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ProductAnomaly"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5921> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5903> ;
    skos:definition "Concrete class inherited from Anomaly abstract class that represents an Anomaly associated with the Resource domain. For example the Anomaly associated with a particular network function KPIs or data streams from a particular IT system.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA16_EA1_EA5921" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ResourceAnomaly"@en .

