<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6017> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6027> ;
    skos:definition "The model below justifies the inclusion of ClosedLoop as a managed entity derived from SID's Entity ABE. A ClosedLoop can have a goal or multiple goals and thus needs a specification to elaborate on its scope of application.<br/>The scope of application of closedLoop can be on any other entity, such as Product, Service, Resource, Customer, Partner based operations. ClosedLoops are also associated to workflows, and typically more than one workflow makes up a ClosedLoop, in that, a ClosedLoop will require a control workflow and a feedback workflow to be complete. The control workflow (controlflow) is responsible for the learning, analysis, and decision-making that enables optimization, planning, and intelligent execution to happen. <br/>A simplified view based on the SID pattern is presented in this figure where ClosedLoop is derived from Root Entity and ClosedLoopSpecification is derived from EntitySpecification. This view presents ClosedLoop as a managed entity, with information required to define and design the closedloop based on a full set of description.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6017" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure CL.01 - Basic Closed Loop"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6019> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6027> ;
    skos:definition "This diagram illustrates the relationships between Activity, Goal, and Workflow. The implication is to state the information relationship between a Goal, that defines the purpose of a Closedloop, the underlying Workflows that manage the control path (controlflow) and feedback paths, as well as scenarios where a unitary Actvity acts in standalone in the Closedloop.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6019" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure CL.02 - Closed Loop SID Pattern"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6021> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6027> ;
    skos:definition "The figure below provides a more detailed view of entities that make up a full Closedloop SID model to support managing ClosedLoop in a lifecycle manager. The pattern shows a defined ClosedLoop that is fully specified based on the ClosedLoopSpecification business entity, and that can be associated with one or more ClosedLoopGoal(s). and a managed state model ClosedLoopState.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6021" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure CL.03 - Detailed Closed Loop"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6023> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6027> ;
    skos:definition "The state model of closedLoop represents the lifecycle from defining a closedLoop, prototyping it ,verifying and cataloguing and putting it into operations. <br/>The simple view presents the high-level states, with the closed loop as a single entity that is managed.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6023" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure CL.04 - ClosedLoop Lifecycle"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6025> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6027> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA18_EA6025" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure CL.05 - Closed Loop Example"@en .

