<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6184> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "There is a distinction between Goal and Metric. This ABE is intended to reflect that distinction, as well as address the need for both. While a GOAL captures information about a target, a METRIC provides the yardstick or unit of measuring such achievement. Goal and Metric work hand-in-hand and each can be managed and modeled independently to bring flexibility to automation. The importance of this ABE is to capture the essence of dynamic goal setup and updates, which is key to enabler higher levels of goals management and goals management automation.<br/><br/>This diagram presents the primary entities to model Goals with support for Goals expressed declaratively.<br/>A goal is a managed entity that has a lifecycle and can be specified. Goals may be synthesized as declarative or imperative (procedural) statements. A declarative view of goals is necessary in order to reason about important properties of goals, while an imperative (procedural) view of goals is necessary to ensure that goals can be achieved efficiently in dynamic environments. In both cases, goals can be specified and performance against them measured via metrics.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6184" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure G.01 - Basic Goal"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6186> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "A goal that is defined and specified may be realized based on different strategies. The statement of a goal includes setting a direction which is the verb that denotes a direction of thought regarding an ambition. e.g. Goals like \"Increase Sales\", \"Reduce Cost\" have a direction which is \"increase\" – an upward positive improvement of sales between the organization and prospective customers, and for \"reduce cost\" a downward or negative improvement of cost towards the company.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6186" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure G.02 - Detailed Goal"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6188> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "This is an illustration to manage the lifecycle of \"Goal\" as a managed entity. It includes the definition and acceptance of a goal, having a goal that is inactive because of a lack of initialization with a time factor or allocation to a goal-owner, the ability to state the goal as in force and be able to suspend the goal when the ambition or aspiration needs holding off due to changes in expectation.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6188" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure G.03 - Goal Lifecycle"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6192> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "Represents the way in which a goal is to be achieved. For some complex goals, a goal can be recursively defined. E.g. Improve customer experience by increasing direct engagement calls to our corporate customers from sales reps in the closest proximity. The goalApproach in this regard is through salesReps with\"close proximity\"<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6192" ;
    skos:prefLabel "GoalApproach"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6193> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "Represents the first and the last location of objects to be communicated. E.g. Send an alert to the customer. In this case, the Direction is towards the Customer and the Customer is the destination.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6193" ;
    skos:prefLabel "GoalDirection"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6194> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "Designates entities that act as instruments to which a goal is to be performed. E.g. Increase revenue of product-x via \"offline shops\". in this case Offline shops\" in this case is a goalInstriument.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6194" ;
    skos:prefLabel "GoalInstrument"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6195> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "Values: true,falseDefault: False"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6195" ;
    skos:prefLabel "GoalMetric"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6196> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "Expresses the relationship between the \"process\" and the environment.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6196" ;
    skos:prefLabel "GoalModel"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6197> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "Represents the beneficiary(s) for the goal.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6197" ;
    skos:prefLabel "GoalPartyRole"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6198> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "Represents all information to elicit the goal.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6198" ;
    skos:prefLabel "GoalSpecification"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6199> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "Represents the relationships between goal specifications.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6199" ;
    skos:prefLabel "GoalSpecificationRelationship"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6200> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "Expresses the relationship between the \"process\" and the environment. This includes relationships between goals. Note, the term \"Process\" used here represents any task/activity/workflow/closedloop, etc.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6200" ;
    skos:prefLabel "GoalStrategy"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6201> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "Represents the classification of the type entities affected by the goal. Usually, a goal may have two types, the object and the entities that exist/must exist for the goal to be achieved. E.g. identify the customer's choice. \"Customer choice\" is a result of the achievement of the goal.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6201" ;
    skos:prefLabel "GoalTargetEntityType"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6202> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "Represents entities affected by the goal.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6202" ;
    skos:prefLabel "GoalTargetPartRole"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6203> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6190> ;
    skos:definition "Represents a classification scheme for goals. This can be based on functional or non-functional, where functional goals underlie services that are expected to be delivered, while non-functional goals refer to expected qualities such as security, safety, performance, usability, flexibility, etc. Other forms of classification are viable, and not mandated by this information model's entity.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6203" ;
    skos:prefLabel "GoalType"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6204> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6191> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6204" ;
    skos:prefLabel "EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA19_EA6204"@en .

