<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA22_EA6380> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA22_EA6347> ;
    skos:definition "A Vertex represents an entity of interest in a Graph and has a type and a label. Typically, it may represent a hardware appliance such as a router, or an Ethernet port slide-in-unit a power supply or even a network domain.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA22_EA6380" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Vertex"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA22_EA6381> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA22_EA6347> ;
    skos:definition "This is an abstract base class that is used to define the common characteristics (attributes, constraints, and relationships) of a Vertex<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA22_EA6381" ;
    skos:prefLabel "VertexSpecification"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA23_EA6382> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA23_EA6398> ;
    skos:definition "Cost represents a set of information that captures the expense needed to be spent by the service provider to acquire, execute, produce, activate, operate or qualify any entity. This Cost can be applied to any Entity or EntitySpecification (Product, Service, Resource or their related specifications as examples). Cost encompasses the amount of money needed in various aspects of a telco's business processes.<br/>The Cost concept can also make use of the Specification Pattern. Per the following diagram, EntitySpecification can have costs, as can an Entity. Given relationships at this level, ProductSpecification and Product have derived relationships with Cost, as can any subclass of EntitySpecification and Entity.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA23_EA6382" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Co.01 - Cost"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA23_EA6384> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA23_EA6398> ;
    skos:definition "Cost can be made up of some number of CostItems. A given CostItem can have a CostItemAllocation, a CostRate and a TaxItem.<br/>Cost can also have some number of PartyRoles involved, such as project managers, accountants, procurement officers, vendors, etc.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA23_EA6384" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Co.02 - Cost Details"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA23_EA6386> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA23_EA6398> ;
    skos:definition "Cost can take on two forms - ActualCost and ProjectedCost per the following diagram.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA23_EA6386" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Co.03 - Actual and Projected Costs"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA23_EA6388> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA23_EA6398> ;
    skos:definition "The following state diagram provides an overview of the allowed states for an ActualCostItem entity.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA23_EA6388" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Co.04 - ActualCostItem State Diagarm"@en .

