    skos:prefLabel "MetricDefinitionRelationship"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4958> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "One business dictionary defines metrics in terms of standards of measurement.1 They go on to define measurement in terms of values and units. Since there is a fundamental need to measure all aspects of enterprises based on Frameworx, the need for a Common Business Entity standardizing what a Metric is in Frameworx has been deemed as essential.<br/>This addendum is organized in two parts—1) the standardized definition of the SID Metric ABE itself, including elaboration on the critical details of the definition, and 2) Best Practices for design and application of specific metrics, both generically and in specific application uses (e.g., Business Metrics, Performance Metrics, Revenue Assurance Metrics, Customer Metrics, Fraud Management Metrics, etc.). The Metric ABE is made up of a number of lower-level ABEs. <br/>The next section describes the SID Metric ABE and its related components. This ABE was developed to support the SID principle of inherent extensibility by employing SID modeling patterns.<br/>It’s in vision that other projects use and specialize the Metric ABE in some way (creating sub-classes and adding new entities) such as PM (Performance Management), RA (Revenue Assurance), SLA (Service Level Agreement), etc.<br/>This guide book describes the Metric ABE in Common Business Entities Domain.<br/>To find the Information framework figure, refer to “GB991 Core Frameworks Concepts and Principles” guide book.<br/>Metric example introduction<br/>All along this guide book, an example is used for illustrating the diagrams.<br/>You will find illustrations after some diagrams using the well-known example of Layer 3 packet round-trip delay (also known as IP packet 2-way delay).<br/>This metric is typically measured using the ping tool, which is based on ICMP echo (request and reply). It is a network-layer metric which impacts application-layer real-time and interactive services, such as voice, video, gaming, web surfing, etc. In turn, this low-level metric may be used in higher-level metrics, characterizing services (RFS and CFS), up to Customer Experience metrics.<br/>The Entity measured by this metric is a pair of IP hosts (any two hosts: servers, end-user devices, routers, switches, fixed/mobile access nodes, gateways, etc.), or more precisely the IP path between them at the time of measurement.<br/>There are many variants regarding the measurement process of this metric: active measurement relying on a ping-like tool which sends timestamped probe packets, or passive measurement, maybe by timestamping real traffic packets. Then there are different options concerning sampling (with or without a measurement session, packet size, packet payload, random or constant spacing of samples when applicable, etc.) and actual implementation of packet timestamping. Clock synchronization is not critical for two-way delay metrics, but it is for one-way delay metrics.<br/>Further details about measurement methodology can be found for instance in TWAMP (Two-Way Active Measurement Protocol) RFCs from the IETF IPPM (IP Performance Metrics) Working Group (http://datatracker.ietf.org/wg/ippm/charter/).<br/>There are similar tools in layer 2 (Ethernet OAM CFM LB (Loop Back: from IEEE 802.1ag or ITU-T Y.1730/1731), LSP ping, PW VCCV) and in layers 4-7 (various proprietary methods including service pings).<br/>______________<br/>1 http://www.businessdictionary.com, Copyright©2007-2011 Vijay Luthra and BusinessDictionary.com. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED.<br/>______________<br/><br/>The core entity in the ABE is MetricDefinition. It provides basic facts that define or specify what a metric is, such as the name, description, and so forth. Any entity in the SID can be measured. The association between MetricDefinition and RootEntityType provides this capability. Instances of RootEntityType represent all the entities in the SID model. The *-* association between these two entities allows the same definition to be used to measure any number of entities in the SID model and for a SID entity to be measured by any number of definitions.<br/>The definition of a metric can also be categorized, such as a business metric, a fraud metric, a revenue assurance metric. The association to MetricDefintionCategory allows many different categorizations of a MetricDefinition via the *-* association. The recursive association on MetricDefinition enables categories to be divided into sub-categories as needed, such as a revenue sub-category of a business metric or a profitability category of a business metric. <br/>MetDefBusinessValue enables multiple relative business values to be associated to the MetricDefinition, such as revenue benefit, cost benefit, efficiency, customer experience, time to market, and so forth.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4958" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.01 - Basic Metric Definition Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4960> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">For the purpose of this example, some assumptions are made:</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">Considering two IP hosts H1 and H2, the measurement system is able to initiate pings from H1.</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">No measurement session is established between H1 and H2.</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">H2 responds to H1 ping requests.</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">The arbitrary sampling choice is to make 100 raw measurements at 1-second intervals, every 15 minutes.</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">Multiple metrics of interest could be derived from the sample batches of 100 values: average, minimum, maximum, different percentiles, etc. Only the Average is illustrated here.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The following illustration explores the classes describing the metric: definition and business value.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The metricLevel optional attribute is set to 1 as an example. If metricLevel is used, the convention governing the numbering scheme should be included in the description (i.e., “low numbers mean high importance”, or vice-versa). </font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Attributes like metricDefinitionStatus and lastUsed are dynamically modified during the lifetime of the object, by other processes which generate attribute-changing events: modification of the metric definition, usage occurrence of the metric, etc.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Finally, the MetDefBusinessValue is a business-oriented complement to the technical-oriented MetricDefinition.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4960" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.01-I01 – MetricDefinition and MetDefBusinessValue"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4962> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">The following illustration shows examples of categories, as instances of MetricDefinitionCategory. </font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Two categories are represented: </font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">CFS-level performance, </font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">and Network-level performance, which covers both Resources and RFSes. </font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\"> “Weekly % of Good Video Sessions for All Users” and “Estimated MOS of a video session” MetricDefinitions would fall within the former category, while “Layer 3 packet roundtrip delay” would fall within the latter. </font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The optional linkageReference attribute would refer to some other categorization approaches such as Frameworx domains or Business Architecture domains. </font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Relationships (possibly hierarchical) between MetricDefinitionCategory instances are possible using the MetricDefinitionCategoryIncludes association: in this example, CFSPerf would “include” NetworkPerf in the sense that CFSPerf metrics rely on NetworkPerf metrics.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4962" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.01-I02 – MetricDefinition and MetricDefinitionCategory"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4964> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "MetricDefinition can be defined for any type of entity that a Metric measures (therefore the association to RootEntityType). The SID uses the EntitySpec/Entity pattern to dynamically instantiate entities. MetricDefinition is used to measure these dynamically defined entities. Therefore the association to Specification (as a base class to ResourceSpec and ServiceSpec) has been included as shown in the following Figure.<br/>There is also option to extend the model by associating MetricDefinition with other entity specifications. <br/>Examples for ProductSpec and PerformanceSpec are shown. MetricDefinition has been sub-classed to explicitly show these two types of MetricDefintions. From an implementation perspective they can be rolled up into MetricDefintion if desired, or MetricDefinition could be rolled down into them. Often application boundaries dictate which of the two approaches to take.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4964" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.01a - Metric Definition and Specifications"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4966> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "Metrics may be calculated in a number of different ways from a simple ratio to a complex expression. Figure Me.02 – Metric Definition Measure shows the entities used to calculate a metric value.<br/>A MetricDefMeasure specifies a measure of a specific aspect of an entity, such as lost packets or dealer sales target achievement.<br/>A MetricDefinition may have many MetricDefMeasures. One example of many is that one measure may be in Fahrenheit and another may be in Centigrade.<br/>Two entities, MetricDefinitionDeterminationMethod and MetricDefinitionMethodArgument support the requirement of different ways to calculate Metrics. <br/>Basic facts about the method, such a type (ratio, sum, and so forth) are contained in the MetricDefinitionDeterminationMethod.<br/>The arguments that represent the expression are contained in one or more MetricDefinitionMethodArgument. An argument may be the same or another MetricDefinition. <br/>For example, a simple ratio of metric definition A divided by metric definition B would be represented by two instances of the arguments. The numerator would be related to metric definition A with a sequence of 1 and an operator of “/”. The denominator would be related to metric definition B with a sequence of 2.<br/>The delimiter attribute, such as “(“and“)”, enables more complex expressions. For example (metric definition A + metric definition C).<br/>When an expression is too complex to represent using the arguments, such as one that includes logic and using other entities) the derivationFormula attribute can contain a reference to logic (code) that performs the calculation.<br/>Remark: An implementation of the model may choose to share same determination method for many metric definition measures. If this is the case then the association would be changed to *-*.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4966" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.02 - Metric Definition Measure"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4968> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">The MetricDefMeasure is essentially a high-level description of the measurement method, while the details are provided in the MetricDefinitionDeterminationMethod. </font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">In this example, the MetricDefinitionMethodArgument class is not used, since the raw sample values are not modeled as actual metrics, and thus have no MetricDefinition.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4968" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.02-I01 – MetricDefMeasure and MetricDefinitionDeterminationMethod"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4970> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "The following Figure shows how a MetricDefinition’s description can be extended as well as dimensional attributes that define a Metric.<br/>The MetDefDescExtension entity enables additional descriptive text, such as references and owner notes, to be defined for a MetricDefinition. The metDefType attribute specifies the type of descriptive text contained in the descriptionExtension attribute. <br/>The four-dimension related entities provide the ability to designate methods of organizing individual metrics into common sets, related by the value of the named dimension. <br/>For example, a metric for revenue–individual instance values of revenue could be organized in the dimension of geography (Region 1 Revenues, Region 2 Revenues, etc.), or by Product (Wireless Revenue, Wire-line Revenue, Broadband Revenue, Advertising Revenue, etc.). <br/>The characteristic term when describing dimension is “by”, as in “Revenue, by Product” or “Revenue, by Region”.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4970" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.03 - Metric Definition Description and Dimension"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4972> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "The following Figure shows how hierarchies of metrics are represented.<br/>MetricDefinitions can be related to one another in a variety of ways. One way is in a hierarchy of definitions, such as a calculation hierarchy. <br/>MetricDefinitionHierarchy provides the ability to define any number of hierarchical relationships. MetricDefinitionHierarchyMember represents the relationship between two MetricDefinitions in a hierarchy, one playing the parent role and the other playing the role of a child. <br/>For example, video sessions, with a synthetic scalar metric such as an estimated MOS (Mean Opinion Score), a number between 1 and 5; the per-session MOS KPI is computed using different low-level counters (packet loss, delay, delay variation, NE port-level frame counters, and so forth. <br/>Another type of relationship could indicate one MetricDefinition has been replaced by another or could be used instead of another.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4972" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.04 - Metric Definition Hierarchy"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4974> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">The following example illustrates two arbitrary metric organizations.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">One of them is hierarchical, and represents a calculation hierarchy related to some performance model, represented here as an instance of MetricDefinitionHierarchy called SPPM. </font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Two other metrics are shown one for a MOS estimation of one video session for one end-user (M2), and another one for an overall synthesis of the performance of a Video Service offered by a Service Provider (M3). M3 is computed from M2, and M2 may involve M1-Avg (in its calculation. </font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">M1-Avg, M2, and M3 are members of that SPPM hierarchy (as indicated by the corresponding instances of MetricDefinitionHierarchyMember), M3 as a parent only, M2 as both a parent and a child, and M1-Avg as a child only.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The other metric organization represents the connection between M1-Avg, M2, and M3 with respect to some service impact model. In this case, the service impact model might be a graph, without an implicit hierarchical tree structure. These relationships are modeled using the MetricDefinitionRelationship construct (associative class). If the service impact model of this example had also been hierarchical, then another instance of MetricDefinitionHierarchy (maybe called SIMM for Service Impact Metric Model) could have been used, with additional instances of MetricDefinitionHierarchyMember for M1-Avg, M2, and M3</font>.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4974" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.04 - I01 – MetricDefinitionHierarchy"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4976> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "Many different parties can be involved with the definition of a metric. Figure Me.05 – Metric Definition Involvement shows the part of the model that represents this involvement.<br/>A Party independent of the role they play can be involved or a role played by a party (PartyRole) can be involved.<br/>The involvementType attribute of MetricDefinitionInvolvement specifies the type of involvement, such as the source, user, owner, defining authority of the MetricDefinition.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4976" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.05 - Metric Definition Involvement"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4978> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">An example of an involvement relating a metric (or rather its MetricDefinition) to a Party or PartyRole is given in following Figure.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The involvement here refers to the responsibility of performing the measurement of the M1-Avg metric and reporting the results, presumably via a measurement system with a GUI for network and service administrators.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">This data model example would represent the point of view of a network operator which would contract a third-party company as a supplier of this measurement and reporting service. </font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Note that the validFor attributes are different in each instance, since they describe the validity period of each object: validity of the metric involvement, validity of the entity modeled as a Party, and validity of the entity PartyRole as a supplier (which may or may not be the same as the validity of the metric involvement).</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4978" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.05 -I01 – MetricDefinitionInvolvement"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4980> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "There is often the need to add additional attributes to the definition of a metric or to add attributes that are specific to an instance of a metric.<br/>The following Figure shows how the Characteristic model can be used to support this requirement. More information on Characteristics can be found in the Root Business Entities guide book.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4980" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.06 - Metric Definition Using Characteristics"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4982> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "The following Figure shows an overview of how threshold are specified for a MetricDefMeasure.<br/>A MetricDefMeasure specifies a measure of a specific aspect of an entity, such as lost packets or dealer sales target achievement, defined for a MetricDefinition that may trigger consequence (s) (MetricDefMeasureConsequence) if a threshold (MetricDefMeasureThreshold) is crossed.<br/>A MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet provides a way to group a set of one or more MetricDefMeasureThresholdRules specifying the condition to evaluate for applying consequences.<br/>The thresholdType specifies the type of MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule contained in the MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet.<br/>The value is “LogicDefinition” if the MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet contains only MetricThresholdRuleDefinition instances and “PreDefined” if it contains only PreDefinedMetricThresholdRule instances.<br/>A MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet is used to evaluate one or more MetricDefMesures.<br/>Threshold rules (MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule) may differ in the condition that they apply, a raise condition or a clear condition, and in the severity of the threshold crossing.<br/>A MetricDefMeasureConsequence defines the action (prescribed action or notification) taken when a MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule is crossed and might depend on MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule applied or not for the previous MetricMeasure..<br/>When a MetricDefMeasureConsequence is applied (track as a MetricMeasureConsequence) this is the result of a single rule (MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule) being crossed.<br/>Different consequences (MetricDefMeasureConsequence) can be defined for different severities. <br/>The repeatAction attribute on MetricDefMeasureConsequence is an indicator used to specify that a consequence <br/> • should cease being applied if a value is in the same range as the previous value<br/> • or continue being applied if a value is in the same range as the previous value.<br/>If the repeatApplication is True, the consequence is always applied as soon as the MetricMeasure value is in the range of values and if the repeatApplication is False, the consequence is applied only if the previous MetricMeasure value wasn’t in the same range.<br/>Nota: <br/> • The two associations pre-fixed by a slash correspond to derived associations.<br/> • A derived association represents synthetically several associations. See example with the next figure.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4982" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.07a - Metric Threshold Definition - Derived Associations"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4984> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "The following Figure shows the detailed associations for MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule.<br/>The MetricDefMeasureThreshConsDependency specifies the type of dependency that may exist between MetricDefMeasureConsequence and MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule. For example, \"the consequence is triggered only if the rule has been applied previously\", or \"if the rule has already been applied then do not trigger the consequence\".<br/>The two associations MetricDefMeasureConsequenceDependentUpon, MetricDefMeasureThresholdRuleDefines and the entity MetricDefMeasureThreshConsDependency are summarized through the derived association “/MetricDefMeasureConsequenceDependsOn” on the Figure Me.07a - Metric Threshold Definition - Derived Associations.<br/>The MetricDefMeasureThresholdConsequence specifies the sequence of application when several MetricDefMeasureConsequence have to be applied for a specific MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule.<br/>The two associations MetricDefMeasureThresholdRuleResultsIn, MetricDefMeasureConsequenceDeterminedBy and the entity MetricDefMeasureThresholdConsequence are summarized through the derived association “/MetricDefMeasureThresholdRuleResultsIn” on the Figure Me.07a - Metric Threshold Definition - Derived Associations.<br/>Note: A derived association enables more synthetic views and is less accurate than the real detailed associations but has not to be implemented.<br/>The MetricDefMeasureThresholdRelationship enables specifying any kind of relationships between MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule such as depends on, follows, and so forth.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4984" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.07b - Metric Definition Threshold Associations"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4986> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "The following Figure shows the detailed view of how threshold are specified for a MetricDefMeasure.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4986" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.07c - Metric Threshold Definition"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4988> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "The following Figure shows the different types of threshold rules that might be defined.<br/>A MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule is a rule that defines the condition (raise or clear) to achieve to apply consequences when a threshold (MetricDefMeasureThreshold) is crossed or ceased to be crossed. It may behave in one of two different ways:<br/> • Either it provides attributes for various kinds of threshold logic definition (MetricThresholdRuleDefinition),<br/> • or it is defined by a derivation algorithm that represents a predefined logic that can be executed with parameters (PreDefinedMetricThresholdRule).<br/>A MetricThresholdRuleDefinition specifies the threshold range of values (lower and upper conformance target) with comparators (lower and upper comparator), tolerances and, grace periods, and a comparator. <br/>Each comparator is an operator that specifies whether MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet is crossed when it is above or below a conformance target. For example, a threshold may specify that when average lost packets indicator exceeds a value of 2000 and is under 3000, then the threshold is crossed.<br/>A PreDefinedMetricThresholdRule is a \"blackbox\" logic and is defined by a named predefined logic that can be executed with parameters. Therefore the PreDefinedMetricThresholdRule entity will hold the rule name, and the PreDefinedMetricThresholdRuleParam will define the parameters that are required for executing the PreDefinedMetricThresholdRule. As these parameters are often indicator specifications, they can be associated to the MetricDefMeasure entity.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4988" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.08 - Metric Definition Measure Threshold Rule"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4990> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">The following examples illustrates the use of MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet, MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet and MetricDefMeasureConsequence.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">A Metric is defined to evaluate the “Average Layer 3 packet roundtrip delay in millisecond”</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">5 value ranges (thresholds) in millisecond are defined for that Metric</font></li></ul><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">[0;100[ Good</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">[100;250[ Acceptable</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">[250;1000[ Bad</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">[1000;+¥[ Very Bad</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">nil value Not measurable </font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">(may be due to problems such as disconnect or due to sensor failure)</font></li></ul><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">for each value range one or more Consequences to trigger might be defined:</font></li></ul><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">[0;100[ Green GUI</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">[100;250[ Green GUI</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">[250;1000[ Light Orange GUI & raise a Warning notification</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">[1000;+¥[ Dark Orange GUI & raise a Major notification</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">nil value Red GUI & trigger the diagnose of “not measurable”</font></li></ul><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">• Some consequences are defined according to the previous measure’s value range</font></li></ul><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">no longer [0;100[ and whatever the new value is notify degradation</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">no longer [1000;+¥[ and new value [0;250[ notify end of Major trouble</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">Rk: To have more simple diagrams the entities used to detail the relationships are not represented (MetricDefMeasureThreshConsDependency and MetricDefMeasureThresholdConsequence) in the illustrations.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Here for any measure in the range of [0;100[ the consequence “update GUI to green” is triggered.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4990" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.07-08-I01 – Simple consequence"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4992> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">According to the previous measure (MetricMeasure) compared to the new measure, a consequence might be triggered.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">In this example, if the previous measure was between 0 to 100 and the new measure is out of this range of values (specified by the “DependsOnPrevious” association), then a notification is sent to alert about the degradation.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4992" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.07-08-I02 – Constraints on consequences"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4994> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">The same rule may trigger several consequences.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Here for any measure in the range of [250;1000[ two consequences are triggered (Light Orange GUI & raise a Warning notification).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">And the same consequence might be re-used.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Here for any measure in the range of [250;1000[ or [100;100[ a Warning is notified.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4994" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.07-08-I03 – Several consequences and re-use"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4996> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">In this example, we assume that the captureFrequency defined by the MetricDefMeasure is 10 seconds. So, we will evaluate 7 measures during 60 seconds.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The tolerancePeriod is 60 seconds and the numberOfAllowedCrossing is 1.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Then if we evaluate the following measures 50, 500, 2000, 100, 60, 80, 90</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">no consequence will be initiated.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">But if the measures are the following 50, 500, 2000, 100, 60, 80, 1500 then the two consequences will be initiated.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Note: When no value is specified for a conformanceTarget Upper or Lower this means it is boundless.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4996" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.07-08-I04 – MetricThresholdRuleDef tolerancePeriod, toleranceNumber"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4998> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Sometimes, the measure is impossible.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">In this case, specific actions (consequences) might be triggered.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Here, adding to the fact that the GUI is changed to Red, a diagnose action is triggered identifying the root cause of the trouble.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4998" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.07-08-I05 – Specific consequences for non-measurable"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5125> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5127> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are business entities aggregated under the <b>Metric Definition Measure Threshold </b>Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5125" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure MDMT.01 - Metric Definition Measure Threshold ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5128> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5127> ;
    skos:definition "A dependency a MetricDefMeasureConsequence has on a MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5128" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricDefMeasureThreshConsDependency"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5129> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5127> ;
    skos:definition "The sequence in which a MetricDefMeasureConsequence should be applied for a MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5129" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricDefMeasureThresholdConsequence"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5130> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5127> ;
    skos:definition "The MetricDefMeasureThresholdRelationship enables specifying any kind of relationships between MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule such as depends on, follows, and so forth.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5130" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricDefMeasureThresholdRelationship"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5131> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5127> ;
    skos:definition "A MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule is a rule that defines the condition (raise or clear) to achieve to apply consequences when a threshold (MetricDefMeasureThreshold) is crossed or ceased to be crossed. It also defines the severity of the raise or clear of the threshold.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5131" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5132> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5127> ;
    skos:definition "A MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet provides a way to group a set of one or more MetricDefMeasureThresholdRules specifying the condition to evaluate for applying consequences.<br/><br/>A MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet is used to evaluate one or more MetricDefMesures.<br/><br/>A MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet contains either MetricThresholdRuleDefinition instances or PreDefinedMetricThresholdRule instances.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5132" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5133> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5127> ;
    skos:definition "This datatype lists the possible severities that can be allocated to a MetricMeasure. Enumeration values (literals) can be added for internal use but added values should be exposed in external interfaces.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5133" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricPerceivedSeverity"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5134> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5127> ;
    skos:definition "List of comparators that can be used to evaluate a value with an other such as equal, greater than, lower than...<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5134" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricThresholdComparator"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5135> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5127> ;
    skos:definition "MetricThreshold Condition may be either Raise or Clear.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5135" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricThresholdCondition"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5136> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5127> ;
    skos:definition "Various types of threshold logic can be implemented by this entity. For example: Indicator #gt; Value.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5136" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricThresholdRuleDefinition"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5137> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5127> ;
    skos:definition "The Threshold Type may be either \"LogicDefinition\" or \"PreDefined\".<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5137" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricThresholdType"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5138> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5127> ;
    skos:definition "A pre-defined threshold is a \"black-box\" logic that resides in the PM Producing Application. A PM consuming application can execute it assigning values to its parameters.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5138" ;
    skos:prefLabel "PreDefinedMetricThresholdRule"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5139> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5127> ;
    skos:definition "The parameters that are associated to a pre-defined threshold.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA1_EA5139" ;
    skos:prefLabel "PreDefinedMetricThresholdRuleParam"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5112> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5114> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are business entities aggregated under the <b>Metric Definition Measure </b>Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5112" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure MDM.01 - Metric Definition Measure ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5115> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5114> ;
    skos:definition "It specifies the invariant characteristics that define a communication (notification) that occurs as part of a MetricDefMeasureConsquence. A Notification is typically one-sided, in that no Response is expected. <br/><br/>For example, a notification might be defined for a supervisor role and another one for a technician role as the result of a MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule.<br/><br/>In this case, each ConsequenceMetricNotificationSpec will specify to include the value of the MetricMeasure but the text might be different and they could contain different information according to the scope of interest from the supervisor and the technician.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5115" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ConsequenceMetricNotificationSpec"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5117> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5114> ;
    skos:definition "How the value of the metric is determined, examples are ratio, formula, algorithm, external call (web service).<br/><br/>This entity is may be further developed to support all determination methods. It may also be further defined and subclassed in the future.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5117" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricDefinitionDeterminationMethod"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5118> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5114> ;
    skos:definition "Arguments needed for the calculation of the metrric definition such as numerator and denominator.<br/><br/>This entity imay be enhanced when MetricDefinitionDeterminationMethod is enhanced. An argument could be a MetricDefinition or a raw counter.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5118" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricDefinitionMethodArgument"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5119> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5114> ;
    skos:definition "A MetricDefMeasure specifies a measure of a specific aspect of an entity, such as lost packets or dealer sales target achievement, defined for a MetricDefinition that may trigger consequence (s) (MetricDefMeasureConsequence) if a threshold (MetricDefMeasureThreshold) is crossed.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5119" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricDefMeasure"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5120> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5114> ;
    skos:definition "The time of day or days during which a MetricDefMeasure is measured or not measured.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5120" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricDefMeasureApplicability"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5121> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5114> ;
    skos:definition "A MetricDefMeasureConsequence defines the action (prescribed action or notification) to take when a MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule is crossed.<br/><br/>The same MetricDefMeasureConsequence might be reused by several MetricDefMeasureThresholdRules.<br/><br/>Different consequences (MetricDefMeasureConsequence) can be defined for different severities.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5121" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricDefMeasureConsequence"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5122> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5114> ;
    skos:definition "MetricDefMeasureExpression describes strict relations between MetricDefMeasure subordinates (MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule, MetricDefMeasureApplicability, MetricDefMeasureConsequence). The baseline idea of MetricDefMeasureExpression is to resolve the multiple associations between MetricDefMeasure subordinates. For example, an expression may consist of a consequence and its applicability for a MetricDefMeasure.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5122" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricDefMeasureExpression"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5123> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5114> ;
    skos:definition "A MetricDefMeasureGroup is a set of MetricDefMeasures, usually reported in the same message by the equipment or the EMS.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5123" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricDefMeasureGroup"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5124> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5114> ;
    skos:definition "The MetricValueType specifies the different possible type of values such as Int, String...<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA4_EA5124" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MetricValueType"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5000> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Other example for a Metric defined to evaluate the “Average Layer 3 packet roundtrip delay in millisecond”</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Exceptions (thresholds) in millisecond are defined for that Metric</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">Normal, 0 =#lt; value #lt; 500, no need to be modeled, as only exceptions are modeled</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">Major, Crosses: 500 =#lt; value, Clear exception: value #lt; 460</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">nil value Not measurable </font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">(may be due to problems such as disconnect or due to sensor failure)</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">For each event of a threshold crossing/ceased to cross one or more Consequences to trigger might be defined:</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">Raise an Alarm of the specific severity</font></li></ul><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">Clear an Alarm of the specific severity</font></li></ul><p/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5000" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.07-08-I06 – Example 2 of rules for a MetricDefMeasure"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5002> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">An alternative solution for this case would be to use the MetricDefMeasureThresholdRelationship as it is represented hereafter.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5002" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.07-08-I07 – Example 2 of rules for a MetricDefMeasure- Alternative Solution"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5004> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "Different kinds of consequences may be applied as a consequence of threshold. The following Figure shows how to describe notification consequences.<br/>A MetricDefMeasureConsequence either results in a prescribed action (prescribedAction) or one or more ConsequenceMetricNotificationSpecs.<br/>If a MetricMeasureConsequence is triggered by a MetricMeasure (through a MetricMeasureThresholfRule) according to a MetricDefMeasureConsequence and the MetricDefMeasureConsequence results in ConsequenceMetricNotificationSpecs, then a ConsequenceMetricNotification is created for each of them.<br/>A ConsequenceMetricConsequence is a type of ConsequenceMetricNotification, which in turn is a type of Notification.<br/>A ConsequenceMetricNotification is described by a ConsequenceMetricNotificationSpec.<br/><i>Note: To be consistent with the pattern Specifcation used for ConsequenceMetricNotificationSpec / ConsequenceMetricNotification, a NotificationSpecification should exist in the Business Interaction ABE. This concept would specify the content pattern for each corresponding notification.</i><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5004" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.09 - Metric Measure Notification definition"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5006> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "The following Figure shows how MetricDefMeasures and MetricMeasures may be grouped when needed.<br/>A MetricDefMeasureGroup is a set of MetricDefMeasures, usually reported in the same message by the equipment or the EMS.<br/>A MetricMeasureGroup is a set of MetricMeasures, usually reported in the same message by the equipment or the EMS.<br/>For example, a server will typically report CPU related metrics in a single message. These metrics may include: Maximum CPU usage, Average CPU usage, System CPU usage and User CPU usage. <br/>Mobile RAN may group related metrics by functional aspects in a technology context such as: LTE Intra-frequency handovers, UMTS Radio Access or NodeB Utilization.<br/>Standard protocols like MTOSI or 3GPP will pack the Metric Group in a single message either the same line in a CSV file or within XML tags when the data format is XML.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5006" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.10 - Metric Measure Definition Groups"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5008> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "The following Figure shows how to define jobs to measure MetricDefMeasures and MetricDefMeasureGroups.<br/>A MetricManagementJob is a management activity that may consist of several steps but is performed as a single logical unit in a Metric context.<br/>It can be a one-time activity or a regular one. In the latter case, a schedule definition is attached to it.<br/>A MetricMeasurementJob always defines a scope of monitored objects using the MonitoredMetricObjectCriteria.<br/>A MetricDefMeasure as well as a MetricDefMeasureGroup may be measured by one or more MetricMeasurementJob.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5008" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.11 - Metric Measurement Job"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5010> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "The following Figure shows the different types of MonitoredMetricObjectCriterion.<br/>A MonitoredMetricObjectCriterion defines the scope of monitored objects for which a MeasurementJob is executed.<br/>The scope is either defined:<br/> • by a filter on a Class (sub-class MonitoredMetricClassCriterion) <br/> • or by a list of instances (sub-class MonitoredMetricInstanceCriterion).<br/>A MonitoredMetricClassCriterion is a type of MonitoredMetricObjectCriterion.<br/>It defines the scope of monitored objects for which a MeasurementJob is executed.by a filter on a class through the relationship with RootEntityType.<br/>A MonitoredMetricInstanceCriterion is a type of MonitoredMetricObjectCriterion.<br/>It defines the scope of monitored objects for which a MeasurementJob is executed by a list of instances through the relationship with one or several RootEntity instances.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5010" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.12 - Monitored Metric Object Criterion"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5012> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "The following Figure shows the different types of MetricMeasurementJob.<br/>A MetricMeasurementJob may be<br/> • either a job for evaluating thresholds defined over MetricDefMeasure (MetricMeasurementThresholdJob),<br/> • a job for producing MetricMesures according to a MetricDefMeasure (MetricMeasurementProductionJob),<br/> • a job for collecting MetricMeasures produced by another job (MetricMeasurementCollectionJob),<br/> • or a job for collecting MetricMeasures produced by another job to make available MetricMeasures for subscribers. (AdhocMetricCollection).<br/>A MetricMeasurementThresholdJob evaluates one MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet.<br/>A MetricMeasurementJob defines a scope of monitored objects using the MonitoredMetricObjectCriteria.<br/>A MetricMeasurementJob also defines a scope of monitored objects using the MonitoredMetricClassCriteria.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5012" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.13 - Metric Threshold Job and MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5014> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "A MetricDefMeasure, MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule or even MetricDefMeasureConsequence might applicable only during certain periods.<br/>In this case, the MetricDefMeasureApplicability is used to specify in detail each applicable period.<br/>The MetricDefMeasureApplicability represents the time of day or days during which a MetricDefMeasure, MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule or even MetricDefMeasureConsequence are measurable or not.<br/>The applicableCode attribute Indicates whether an instance represents applicability or un-applicability.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5014" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.14 - Metric Applicability"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5016> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "The following Figure shows how the relationships with MetricDefMeasures might be refined.<br/>For example, a MetricDefMeasureExpression might enable specifying a specific period of applicability or un-applicability (MetricDefMeasureApplicability) for MetricDefMeasureConsequence and / or MetricDefMeasureDefMeasureThresholdRule in the context of a specific MetricDefMeasure.<br/>This capability is useful as MetricDefMeasureConsequence and MetricDefMeasureDefMeasureThresholdRule are reusable by several MetricDefMeasure.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5016" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.15 - Metric Measure Definition Expression"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5018> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "Once metrics are defined the values associated with them can be captured. Figure Me.21 – Metric shows the MetricMeasure entity and its directly related entities.<br/>The MetricMeasure might be collected for 0..1 RootEntity because some entities may be explicitly related to a MetricMeasure, such as those entities currently in the Performance, including Service and Resource, and SLA entities, including ProductOfferingSpecification and ServiceSpecification. These explicit associations represent a more detailed association than the more general association to RootEntity.<br/>This diagram uses RootEntity as an abstract concept showing how any entity can be associated to MetricMeasure.<br/>Since RootEntity is also a real class in the SID model and is the base class of several ABEs (Resource, ResourceSpec, Service, ServiceSpec and Policy) this diagram also includes examples on how to model Metrics that measure entities which are not subclasses of RootEntity in the SID model. <br/>For example, suppose there is a need to collect a metric for the Service instance of RootEntityType. The first step is to select one of the MetricDefinition(s) for it, then the MetricDefMeasure to use, then the MetricDefinitionDeterminationMethod. <br/>The MetricMeasure is associated to the method and to RootEntity (not RootEntityType) that represents for example the instance of Service for which the MetricMeasure is being collected. <br/>There are indirect associations (i.e. derived) from the MetricMeasure to the MetricDefMeasure via the association to MetricDefinitionDeterminationMethod and from MetricMeasure to MetricDefinition via its association to MetricDefMeasure.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5018" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.16 - Basic Metric Measure Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5020> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "A MetricDefMeasure specifies a measure of a specific aspect of an entity, such as lost packets or dealer sales target achievement, defined for a MetricDefinition that may trigger consequence (s) (MetricDefMeasureConsequence) if a threshold (MetricDefMeasureThreshold) is crossed.<br/>A MetricMeasure is a numerical value or text determined for a MetricDefMeasure that may be collected for a RootEntity, such as a connection or a dealer.<br/>A MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet provides a way to group a set of one or more MetricDefMeasureThresholdRules specifying the condition to evaluate for applying consequences.<br/>A MetricDefMeasureThresholdSet is used to evaluate one or more MetricDefMesures.<br/>Threshold rules (MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule) may differ in the condition that they apply, a raise condition or a clear condition, and in the severity of the threshold crossing.<br/>A MetricDefMeasureConsequence defines the action taken when a MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule is crossed.<br/>Different consequences (MetricDefMeasureConsequence) can be defined for different severities. <br/>A MetricMeasureThresholdRule specifies the MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule whose threshold has been crossed by a MetricMeasure.<br/>It triggers one or more MetricMeasureConsequences.For example, the prescribed action by a consequence might be to monitor the MetricMeasure more closely or to notify a specific person or the lost packets MetricMeasure with a value of 2500 would be associated with the threshold of no more than 2000 lost packets through a MetricMeasureThresholdRule.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5020" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.17 - Metric Threshold"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5022> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">The following examples illustrates how the consequences are triggered according to the MetricDefMeasureThrsesholdRule applicable.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Here a MetricMeasure has been measured with a value of 50. </font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">As 50 is between 0 and 100, the consequence resulting from the Avg L3 (ms) Delay Good MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule is triggered.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5022" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.17-I01 – MetricMeasure and triggered consequence"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5024> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">In this example, a second measure with a value of 500 has been measured.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">As 500 is between 250 and 1000, the consequence resulting from Avg L3 (ms) Delay Bad MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule is triggered according to the fact that the previous MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule applied was the Avg L3 (ms) Delay Good.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5024" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.17-I02 –Consequence depends on previous rule"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5026> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">In this example, a third measure with a value of 1500 has been measured.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">As 1500 is upper than1000, the two consequences resulting from Avg L3 (ms) Delay Very Bad MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule are triggered.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5026" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.17-I03 – Several consequences triggered for a MetricMeasure"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5028> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">This example is a second example for applying the depends that can exist between MetricMeasureConsequence and MetricDefMeasureThresholdRule.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5028" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.17-I04 – Consequence depends on previous rule"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5030> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
    skos:definition "A MetricMeasurementJob might be triggered by the schedule or might be triggered by a request from a PartyRole.<br/>In both cases, a MetricMeasurementObservation tracks each measurement (i.e. execution of a MetricMeasurementJob).<br/>A MetricMeasurementObservation represents the contextual information of a measurement such as the observation period, the MetricMeasurementJob used, the requester of the observation (PartyRole) and the scope of the observation through the related MonitoredMetricObjectCriteria.<br/>The MonitoredMetricObjectCriteria related to MetricMeasurementObservation has to be equal to or a sub-set of the one related to the concerned MetricMeasurementJob.<br/>A MetricMeasurementObservation also specifies the MectricMeasures resulting from this observation.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5030" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Me.18 - Metric Observation"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5033> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA10_EA9_EA5032> ;
