    skos:prefLabel "ImageAsset"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1065> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1054> ;
    skos:definition "MarketingCampaigns promote a product through different media, including television, radio, print and online platforms. Campaigns don't have to rely solely on advertising and can also include demonstrations, word of mouth and other interactive techniques. Businesses operating in highly competitive markets may initiate frequent marketing campaigns and devote significant resources to generating brand awareness and sales.<br/><br/>Marketing campaigns can be designed with different goals in mind, including building a brand image, introducing a new product, increasing sales of a product already on the market, or even reducing the impact of negative news. Defining a campaign's goal usually dictates how much marketing is needed and what media are most effective.<br/><br/>A MarketingCampaign specifies<br/><br/> • the Budget allocated, forcasted and achieved,<br/><br/> • the targeted Parties (PartyProfile),<br/><br/> • the SaleChannel and the CommunicationMode or Media to be used,<br/><br/> • the ProductSpecification and ProductOffering it gives away or aims to place,<br/><br/> • the creative used during the campaign (Document and DocumentSpecification),<br/><br/> • and the MktCampaignRules such as rules that will be evaluated for triggering an event-based Marketing Campaign.<br/><br/>A MarketingCampaign is managed by a MktCampaigneManager and designed by a MktCampaignOperator.<br/><br/>A MarketingCampaign is split into waves (MktCampaignWave).<br/><br/>A Marketing Campaign is described in a marketing campaign brief (Document) which describes all the information required to prepare the campaign.<br/><br/>The brief puts the campaign into context and sets campaign objectives. It brings together the information necessary to create a campaign:<br/><br/> • Campaign objectives which are the smallest level of the hierarchy of marketing objectives. They deal with the selected actions to attempt to reach the marketing objectives defined at the Marketing plan level (e.g. action such as sale of an option, stimulate usage, retain with promotions, sale of a mobile or accessories, optimize ARPU, …);<br/><br/> • Metrics and KPIs to measure the performance of a campaign based on MktIndicatorSpec referring to quantitative data such as proposition take rate or click-through objectives for example (achieve a click-through rate of 4% or higher, achieve a proposition take rate of 1.5% or higher, ….);<br/><br/> • a target market which is composed by party segments;<br/><br/> • a message based on a general idea or sentence that summarises what you want to say to the customers;<br/><br/> • a budget which is the smallest part of a marketing plan budget allocated at a campaign;<br/><br/> • propositions based on offer specification or/and product specification.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1065" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MarketingCampaign"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1066> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1054> ;
    skos:definition "A characteristic quality or distinctive feature of a MarketingCampaign. The characteristic can be take on a discrete value, such as number of press releases, can take on a range of values, (for example, number of prospects reached 50,000 - 100,000), or can be derived from a formula (for example, number of brokerage house pickups = sum of all brokerage house instance characteristics).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1066" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MarketingCampaignCharacteristic"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1067> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1054> ;
    skos:definition "A number or text that can be assigned to a MarketingCampaignCharacteristic.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1067" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MarketingCampaignCharacteristicValue"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1068> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1054> ;
    skos:definition "Values: true,falseDefault: False"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1068" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MktCampaignRule"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1069> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1054> ;
    skos:definition "In a multichannel campaign management system, marketing campaign management requires to subdivide a campaign in several marketing campaign wave. A marketing campaign wave should use one communication mode and one target. It could be outbound or inbound.<br/><br/>The MktCampaignWave is the smallest operational subdivision of a campaign, with a unique target (set of segmentation criteria to define which persons or legal entities to reach), unique interaction channel (1014, 3000, external call-center), media (ads in a newspaper, ads in the subway…), a duration. It may be inbound (people try to reach the CSP) or outbound (te CSP tries to reach them).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1069" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MktCampaignWave"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1070> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1054> ;
    skos:definition "A WaveList corresponds to the split of a MarketingCampaign’s target in waves. The reason of the split might be:<br/><br/> • temporal splitting: wave recurrence, (ex: a non-recurrent Wave has only one Wave’s Recurrence);<br/><br/> • technical splitting (ex: limited volume in email sending, SMS sending…).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA5_EA1070" ;
    skos:prefLabel "WaveList"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1071> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1073> ;
    skos:definition "A MetricDefinition defines for an Entity a group of measures with targeted values and associated actions when the thresholds aren’t respected (MetricSpecMeasure).<br/>A MetricMeasurementObservation calculates for an instance of Entity for a specific period, the values of measures that helps identifying actions to be applied when the thresholds aren’t respected (MetricMeasure).<br/>A MetricMeasurementObservation is described by a MetricDefinition.<br/>A MetricMeasure is described by a MetricDefMeasure.<br/>Marketing objective is a set of action in charge of to specify, CSP communications and presence according to strategic axes, to support product <font color=\"#29313b\">(i.e. ProductSpecification or ProductOfferingSpecification) </font>introductions and specific promotions to sell products, retain customers, and bring in new customers.<br/>Example:<br/><ul><li>drive profitable sales with marketing objectives such as sell on value, promote strategic products, improve sales cycle…</li><li>grow customer profitability with marketing objectives such as retain & grow strategic accounts, customer P&L sales focus…</li></ul>MarketingObjectiveDefinition is defined by metrics to evaluate with threshold that must be achieved and possibly actions that must be applied when the thresholds are not achieved. These metrics and thresholds are specified with MarketingIndicatorDef.<br/>MarketingObjectiveDefinition is a type of MetricDefinition.<br/>Each MarketingObjectiveDefinition might take part in one or many MarketingObjectiveDefinitions.<br/>A MarketingIndicatorDefinition is a type of MetricDefMeasure in the context of OperationalMarketingPlans and / or MarketingCampaigns.<br/>A MarketingObjectiveMeasure is a type of MetricMeasurementObservation described by a MarketingObjectiveDefinition and containing one or many MarketingIncators.<br/>A MarketingIndicator is a type of MetricMeasure described by MarketingIndicatorDefinition that contains the result of a MaktIndicatorDefinition’s evaluation for an instance of Entity for a specific period.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1071" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure MP.01 - Marketing Objective and measures"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1074> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1073> ;
    skos:definition "A MarketingIndicator is a type of MetricMeasure described by MarketingIndicatorDefinition that contains the result of MarketingIndicatorDefinition's evaluation for an instance of Entity for a specific period.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1074" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MarketingIndicator"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1075> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1073> ;
    skos:definition "A MarketingIndicatorDefinition specifies a metric measure. It specifies measure (how to calculate it) with targeted values and associated actions when the thresholds aren’t achieved. <br/><br/>The MarketingIndicatorDefinitions are used to define objectives of OperationalMarketingPlans and MarketingCampaigns such as performance or budget objectives.<br/><br/>MarketingIndicatorDefinition is a type of MetricDefMeasure.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1075" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MarketingIndicatorDefinition"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1076> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1073> ;
    skos:definition "MarketingObjectiveDefinition is a set of actions in charge of to specify, CSP communications and presence according to strategic axes, to support product introductions and specific promotions to sell products, retain customers, and bring in new customers.<br/><br/>Example:<br/><br/> • drive profitable sales with marketing objectives such as sell on value, promote strategic products, improve sales cycle…<br/><br/> • grow customer profitability with marketing objectives such as retain & grow strategic accounts, customer P&L sales focus…<br/><br/>MarketingObjectiveDefinition is defined by metrics to evaluate with threshold that must be achieved and possibly actions that must be applied when the thresholds are not achieved. These metrics and thresholds are specified with MktIndicatorDefinition.<br/><br/>MarketingObjectiveDefinition is a type of MetricDefinition.<br/><br/>Each MarketingObjectiveDefinition might take part in one or many MarketingObjectiveDefinitions.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1076" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MarketingObjectiveDefinition"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1077> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1073> ;
    skos:definition "Values: true,falseDefault: False"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA6_EA1077" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MarketingObjectiveMeasure"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA7_EA1078> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA925> ;
    skos:definition "<b>Market Sales Forecast ABE </b>maintains market forecasts, new service requirements, customer needs, and customer education.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA7_EA1078" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Market Forecast ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA8_EA1079> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA8_EA1081> ;
    skos:definition "A MarketStatistic tracks performance measurements (some of which represent Key Marketing Performance Indicators, or KPIs) for both a service provider and a service provider’s Competitors via an association to PartyRole. Performance measurements include churn and retention, usage patterns, take rates (procurement of a <font color=\"#29313b\">ProductOfferingSpecification</font> by the market), and market penetration. Any mix of <font color=\"#29313b\">ProductOfferingSpecification</font>s andalterations, MarketSegments, SalesChannels, and GeographicAreas can categorize the statistics over any time period. The figure below shows MarketStatistic and its related entities. <br/>When a MarketStatistic represents a KPI, the CompositeMarketStatistic can be used to represent a roll-up of statistics. For example, manager level statistics can roll up to director level statistics, which in turn can roll up to enterprise officer level statistics.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA8_EA1079" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure MS.07 - Market Statistics and Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA8_EA1082> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA8_EA1081> ;
    skos:definition "A type of MarketStatistic that does not have any subordinate MarketStatistics, that is, an AtomicMarketStatistic is a leaf-level MarketStatistic.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA8_EA1082" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AtomicMarketStatistic"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA8_EA1083> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA8_EA1081> ;
    skos:definition "A type of MarketStatistic that is formed by aggregating other MarketStatistics, which may be Composite or Atomic MarketStatistics.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA8_EA1083" ;
    skos:prefLabel "CompositeMarketStatistic"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA8_EA1084> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA8_EA1081> ;
    skos:definition "A categorization of performance measures by MarketSegment. Performance is measured for the ServiceProvider and a ServiceProvider's Competitors in the market place.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA8_EA1084" ;
    skos:prefLabel "MarketStatistic"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA921> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA925> ;
    skos:definition "The diagram below lists the Market Domain's ABEs.<br/><b>Market Party Roles ABE</b><br/><ul><li>Market Party Roles ABE contains all PartyRoles related to the Market Domain such as MarketingManager and MarketingDesigner.</li></ul><b>Market Segment ABE</b><br/><ul><li>Market Segment ABE contains all information for grouping of Parties via concepts such as GeographicAreas or SalesChannels. MarketSegments are the target of MarketingCampaigns and ProductOfferingSpecifications.</li></ul><b>Competitor ABE</b><br/><ul><li>The Competitor ABE identifies other providers who compete in the same market segments, accumulates intelligence about the competitors, including products (price, Key Performance Indicators and so forth).</li><li>The Competitor ABE provides information relative to the analysis of intelligence pertaining to an enterprise’s competitors. It is crucial to understand who the competitors are, what their products are, what the target markets for their products are, and how successful their products are.</li></ul><b>Market Strategy Plan ABE</b><br/><ul><li>Market Strategy Plan ABE supports the business plans and strategies on how to address the market with appropriate products and channels.</li></ul><b>Marketing Campaign ABE</b><br/><ul><li>The Marketing Campaign ABE represents the strategy, or approach, for marketing new or existing ProductOfferingSpecifications to identified target markets.</li></ul><b>Marketing Performance ABE</b><br/><ul><li>Marketing Performance ABE contains all information used to define Marketing performance objectives and Marketing indicators measured.</li></ul><b>Market Forecast ABE (not fully developed)</b><br/><ul><li>Market Forecast ABE maintains market forecasts, new service requirements, customer needs, and customer education.</li></ul><b>Market Statistics ABE (not fully developed)</b><br/><ul><li>The Market Statistics maintains market key performance indicators about Marketing revenue.</li></ul><p/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA921" ;
    skos:prefLabel "[MD-01] Market ABEs Level 1"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA923> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA925> ;
    skos:definition "The diagram below lists the Market & Sales Domain's ABEs Level 1 & 2.<br/><b>Competitor Intelligence ABE</b><br/><ul><li>Competitor Intelligence ABE contains facts gathered about a Competitor's plans and activities. These facts can be used to perform Competitor SWOT analysis in order to better understand a Competitor.</li></ul><b>Competitor Product Correlation ABE</b><br/><ul><li>Competitor Product Correlation ABE contains a variety of Product domain ABEs relative to Competitors</li></ul><p/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA1_EA923" ;
    skos:prefLabel "[MSD-02] Market ABEs Level 1 & 2"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA2_EA1085> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA895> ;
