<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1198> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1204> ;
    skos:definition "The Customer Domain party roles presently identified are:<br/> • Customer: A person or organization that buys products from the enterprise or receives free offers or products. This is modelled as a Party playing the role of Customer. A Customer is a type of PartyRole. Customers can also be other service providers who resell the enterprises products, other service providers that lease the enterprise's resources for utilization by the other service provider's products and services, and so forth.<br/> • Buyer: A PartyRole played by a Party, who imposed a Supplier to provide a deliverable by a formal Agreement (Commitment).<br/> • CustomerServiceRepresentative: Agreed & done: CustomerServiceRepresentative (CSR) is an Employee from the Operator or Dealer. A CSR is in charge of customer relationship, may act on behalf of the customer for sales and in support of the customer.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1198" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure C.00 - Customer Party Roles"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1200> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1204> ;
    skos:definition "Customers are at the center of any enterprise. Without customers at some point in its like, an enterprise cannot exist. Within the SID model, quite a bit of what is normally thought of as customer data resides within the Party business entity. This data includes attributes that describe individuals and organizations, such as name, address, phone, fax, email, and other contact information. More specifically, the role object model is used to abstract the notion of a “customer” into a specific subclass of PartyRole, which is documented in GB922 Party Guide Book. This is shown in Figure C.01 below.<br/>This makes the Customer model inherently extensible. Customers can be conceptualized as an Individual, a group of people, or an organization. By making Customer a subclass of PartyRole, the SID avoids “hard-wiring” specific people or organizations as “customers”. Rather, the SID enables Customer to be one of possibly many roles played.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1200" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure C.01 - Customer as a Type of Party Role"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1202> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1204> ;
    skos:definition "The Following Figure “C.02 – Customer Business Entities” presents the Customer main entities.<br/>The primary business entities in the Customer Data model are Customer and Customer Account. Additional business entities, unique to a given enterprise, can be added to extend this model.<br/>A Customer may possess one or many CustomerBillingAccounts. <br/>A CustomerBillingAccount is an arrangement that a Customer has with an enterprise (such as a communication service provider) through which the enterprise collects AppliedCustomerBillingRate (i.e. charges) to structure bills. It also collects payments for Products that are supplied by the enterprise to the Customer. The AppliedCustomerBillingRates are invoiced to the CustomerBillingAccount via CustomerBills.<br/>A CustomerBillingAccount is a type of Account.<br/>A Customer might be evaluated for its worthiness (PartyCreditProfile) and this evaluation might be based on external information (PartyCreditProfileReference).<br/>The AccountContact qualifies for an Account a contact point (PartyRole and ContactMedium) such as primary, secondary, and emergency contact.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1202" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure C.02 - Customer Business Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1205> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1204> ;
    skos:definition "A PartyRole played by a Party, who imposed a Supplier to provide a deliverable by a formal Agreement (Commitment).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1205" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Buyer"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1206> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1204> ;
    skos:definition "A person or organization that buys products from the enterprise or receives free offers or products. This is modeled as a Party playing the role of Customer. A Customer is a type of PartyRole. Customers can also be other service providers who resell the enterprises products, other service providers that lease the enterprise's resources for utilization by the other service provider's products and services, and so forth.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1206" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Customer"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1207> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1204> ;
    skos:definition "CustomerServiceRepresentative (CSR) is an Employee from the Operator or Dealer. A CSR is in charge of customer relationship, may act on behalf of the customer for sales and in support of the customer.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA1_EA1207" ;
    skos:prefLabel "CustomerServiceRepresentative"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1208> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1230> ;
    skos:definition "A Customer might place orders with the Service Provider. This is represented by the CustomerProductOrder.<br/>CustomerProductOrder / CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem / CustomerProductOrderItem are sub-classes from the pattern ProductOrder / ProductOfferingOrderItem / ProductOrderItem. For further details about ProductOrder / ProductOfferingOrderItem / ProductOrderItem refer to the Product Domain guide book section Product Order ABE.<br/>A ProductOrder represents a request used to procure, update or remove one or many ProductOfferingInstances in the context of a ProductOfferingSpecification through all its ProductOfferingOrderItems.<br/>The particularity of the CustomerProductOrder is to procure, update or remove ProductOfferingInstances for Customer even if, for example, the CustomerProductOrder might be placed by the Service Provider when applying precautionary measures in case of bad debt.<br/>At least one CommunicationInteraction is the source of a CustomerProductOrder. Then, additional interactions might happen such as the Customer asking why his order isn’t yet delivered or the Service Provider informing the Customer his order is completed.<br/>A CustomerProductOrder uses a SalesChannel to be requested.<br/>A CustomerProductOrder might refer to an ImplementationAgreement specifying all what has been approved by the PartyRoles involved in the CustomerProductOrder.<br/><br/>One or many PartyRoles might be involved in a CustomerProductOrder / CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem / CustomerProductOrderItem such as Distributor, Holder, Buyer, Product User or DeliveryDriver.<br/>The CustomerProductOrder and CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem<font color=\"#ff0000\"> </font>may specify the CustomerBillingAccount to which the ProductsOfferingInstances’ are charged to.<br/>When CustomerProductOrder / CustomerProductOfferingOrderItems / CustomerProductOrderItems are not charged to a CustomerBillingAccount and carry one-time charges, they might be directly paid through one or many CustomerPayments.<br/>A CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem may need other CustomerProductOfferingOrderItems to be completed; this dependency is represented through the \"/CustomerProductOfferingOrderItemRefrencesReferencedBy\" relationship. For example, using this relationship you can specify that CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem “2 hours call bundle” requires CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem “Mobile Line”.<br/>A CustomerProductOrderItem may need other CustomerProductOrderItems to be completed; this dependency is represented through the \"/CustomerProductOrderItemRefrencesReferencedBy\" relationship.<br/>A CustomerProductOrder<font color=\"#00ff7f\">,</font> CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem and CustomerProductOrderItems might be further described by Attachments.<br/><i>Relationships with SalesChannel, CustomerBillingAccount and CustomerPayment are not shared with Business Partner orders.</i><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1208" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure C.03 - Customer Product Order Business Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1210> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1230> ;
    skos:definition "CustomerProductOrder is illustrated through several examples (see Figure C03 - Illustration 02, Figure C03 - Illustration 03 and Figure C03 - Illustration 04).<br/>This examples are based on a fictive operator called \"Greenfield\". This operator proposes the ProductOfferingSpecifications described in this figure and Figure C03 - Illustration 01.02.<br/>The offer described in this figure corresponds to the Premium Postpaid Mobile Line CompositeProductOfferingSpecification.<br/>This offer contains a mandatory Premium Mobile Line Offer that corresponds to an AtomicProductOfferingSpecification. This offers makes available the same Mobile Line NetworkProductSpecification than the Mobile Line AtomicProductOfferingSpecification (See Figure C.03 - Illustration 01.02).<br/>The Premium Postpaid Mobile Line CompositeProductOfferingSpecification includes also a mandatory Unlimited National Voice AtomicProductOfferingSpecification. This Unlimited National Voice offer contains an Unlimited National Voice UsageVolumeProductSpec.<br/>The Premium Postpaid Mobile Line composite offer's recurring tariffs are defined at composite offer level.<br/>Premium Mobile Line atomic offer uses the same SMS tariff than the Mobile Line AtomicProductOfferingSpecification (See Figure C.03 - Illustration 01.02).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1210" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure C.03 - Illustration 01.01: \"Greenfield\" Premium Mobile Line Offer"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1212> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1230> ;
    skos:definition "CustomerProductOrder is illustrated through several examples (see Figure C03 - Illustration 02, Figure C03 - Illustration 03 and Figure C03 - Illustration 04).<br/>This examples are based on a fictive operator called \"Greenfield\". This operator proposes the ProductOfferingSpecification described in this figure and in figure NEW Figure C03 - Illustration 01.01: \"Greenfield\" Premium Postpaid Mobile Line Offer.<br/>The offer, described in this figure, corresponds to the Postpaid Mobile Line CompositeProductOfferingSpecification.<br/>This offer contains a mandatory Mobile Line Offer that corresponds to an AtomicProductOfferingSpecification. This offers makes available a Mobile Line NetworkProductSpecification.<br/>The Postpaid Mobile Line Offer CompositeProductOfferingSpecification also includes an optional Extra National Voice AtomicProductOfferingSpecification. This Extra National Voice offer contains an Extra National Voice UsageVolumeProductSpec. This product has an Extra National Voice Volume ProductSpecCharacteristic that can take three possible values (ProductSpecCharacteristicValue): 1, 2 or 5 hours.<br/>For the Postpaid Mobile Line composite offer, prices are defined at included atomic offers levels.<br/>Mobile Line atomic offer has associated recurrent tariff, national voice usage tariff and SMS tariff.<br/>Extra National Voice atomic offer has a recurrent tariff that depends on the value of the Extra National Voice Volume ProductSpecCharacteristic.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1212" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure C.03 - Illustration 01.02: \"Greenfield\" Postpaid Mobile Line Offer"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1214> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1230> ;
    skos:definition "This illustration provides a very simplified example related to CustomerProductOrder.<br/>The company \"Greenfield\" plays the role of Operator (PartyRole). It markets a Pospaid Mobile Line CompositeProductOfferingSpecification.<br/>This offer packages a mandatory Mobile Line AtomicProductOfferingSpecification and an optional Extra National Voice AtomicProductOfferingSpecification.<br/>The Mobile Connectivity Offer makes the Mobile Connectivity NetworkProductSpecification (specialization of AtomicProductSpecification) available.<br/>The Extra National Voice offer makes the Extra National Voice UsageVolumeProductSpecification (inherits from AtomicProductSpecification) available.<br/>M. John Smiths plays the role of Customer. He orders, on the 1st of June 2025, the Mobile Connectivity and the optional Extra National Voice offer with a volume of 5 hours of local calls.<br/>His CustomerProductOrder concerns only one CompositeProductOfferingSpecification. So, one CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI1) will be created. It will concern the Mobile CompositeProductOfferingSpecification. The corresponding action performed by this CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem will correspond to a creation (\"create\") of a CompositeProductOfferingInstance (John Smith's Postpaid Mobile Line offer Instance) with its associated tariffs (example: recurring and one-time fees for mandatory contained ProductOfferingInstances).<br/>The CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI1) will include two associated CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem, one (CPOOI1.1) for the Mobile Line AtomicProductOfferingSpecification and one (CPOOI1.2) for the Extra National Voice AtomicProductOfferingSpecification.<br/>The CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI1.1) will trigger the creation of the Mobile Line AtomicProductOfferinginstance and its associated tariffs (example: usage tariff outside local calls free minutes).<br/>The CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI1.2) will trigger the creation of the Extra National Voice AtomicProductOfferingInstance and its associated tariffs (example: monthly recurring fee).<br/>CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI1.1) is decomposed into one CustomerProductOrderItem (CPOI1.1.1) that will trigger the creation of the John Smith's Mobile Line NetworkProduct.<br/>CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI1.2) is decomposed into one CustomerProductOrderItem (CPOI1.2.1) that will trigger the creation of the John Smith's Extra National Voice UsageVolumeProduct with the value \"5\" for the Extra National Voice Product Volume characteristic value.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1214" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure C.03 - Illustration 02: CompositeProductOfferingSpecification Customer Order"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1216> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1230> ;
    skos:definition "This illustration provides a very simplified example related to CustomerProductOrder.<br/>On the previous illustration (Figure C03 - Illustration 02), M. John Smith ordered a mobile offer and an Extra National Voice option with a volume of 5 hours.<br/>In this illustration, M. John Smith cancels, on the 12th of September 2025, his Extra National Voice option.<br/>M. John Smiths plays the role of Customer. He orders a cancellation of the optional Extra National Voice offer and products.<br/>His CustomerProductOrder concerns only one CompositeProductOfferingSpecification. So, one CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI2) will be created. It will concern the Postpaid Mobile Line CompositeProductOfferingSpecification and associated CompositeProductOfferingInstance. It will Modify the content of the CompositeProductOfferingInstance.<br/>The CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI2) will include one associated CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI2.1) for the Extra National Voice AtomicProductOfferingSpecification cancellation.<br/>The CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI2.1) will trigger the cancelation of the Extra National Voice AtomicProductOfferingInstance and its associated tariffs.<br/>CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI2.1) is decomposed into one CustomerProductOrderItem (CPOI2.1.1) that will trigger the cancelation of the John Smith's Extra National Voice UsageVolumeProduct.<br/>The validFor attributes of the corresponding AtomicProductOfferingInstance and UsageVolumeProduct are modified to show that they are not valid anymore after the 12th of September 2025.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1216" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure C.03 - Illustration 03: AtomicProductOfferingInstance Cancel Customer Order"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1218> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1230> ;
    skos:definition "This illustration provides another very simplified example related to CustomerProductOrder.<br/>On the previous illustration (Figure C03 - Illustration 03), M. John Smith canceled his Extra National Voice option.<br/>In this illustration, M. John Smith decides to migrate from the standard Postpaid Mobile Line offer to a Premium Postpaid Mobile Line offer, on the 1st of October 2025. This offer proposes a Premium Mobile Line AtomicProductOfferingSpecification and an Unlimited National Voice AtomicProductOfferingSpecification.<br/>M. John Smiths plays the role of Customer. His orders the migration from standard Postpaid Mobile Line to Premium Postpaid Mobile Line offer.<br/>His CustomerProductOrder concerns only one CompositeProductOfferingSpecification. So, one CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI3) will be created. It will concern the Premium Postpaid Mobile Line CompositeProductOfferingSpecification and create the associated CompositeProductOfferingInstance with its RecurringProdPriceCharge corresponding to the monthly rental fee. It will use the the \"Standard to Premium Migration\" ProductOfferingSpecificationMigration subtype of AllowedProductAction to create the Premium Postpaid Mobile Line CompositeProductOfferingInstance and cancel the existing Pospaid Mobile Line CompositeProductOfferingInstance.<br/>The CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI3) will include two associated CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem. One to migrate to the Premium Mobile Line AtomicProductOfferingSpecification (CPOOI3.1) and one for the Unlimited National Voice AtomicProductOfferingSpecification creation (CPOOI3.2).<br/>The CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI3.1) will trigger the migration from the Pospaid Mobile Line AtomicProductOfferingInstance to the Premium Pospaid Mobile Line AtomicProductOfferingInstance. This will correspond to the cancellation of the Pospaid Mobile Line AtomicProductOfferingInstance and the creation of the Premium Pospaid Mobile Line AtomicProductOfferingInstance with its associated ProductPrice (here, a UsageProdPriceCharge for SMS rating).<br/>The validFor attribute of the previous Mobile Line Offer AtomicProductOfferingInstance is modified to show that it is not valid anymore after the 1st of October 2025.<br/>The existing Mobile Line NetworkProduct remains unmodified as the same product is used for both Mobile Line AtomicProductOfferingInstance and Premium Mobile Line AtomicProductOfferingInstance.<br/>The CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI3.2) will trigger the creation of the Unlimited National Voice AtomicProductOfferingInstance and its associated tariffs.<br/>CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem (CPOOI3.2) is decomposed into one CustomerProductOrderItem (CPOI3.2.1) that will trigger the creation of the John Smith's Unlimited National Voice UsageVolumeProduct.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1218" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure C.03 - Illustration 04: Migration Customer Order"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1220> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1230> ;
    skos:definition "One or many PartyRoles might be involved in a CustomerProductOrder / CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem / CustomerProductOrderItem such as Distributor, Holder, Buyer or Product User.<br/>Each CustomerProductOrderItem requires an action (AllowedProductAction) on a ProductSpecification<br/>The configuration required is described by the related Product even if it isn’t delivered yet. <br/>To deliver the corresponding Product, the Place to deliver and Appointment(s) might be needed. An Appointment is an arrangement to do something or meet someone at a particular time and location.<br/>CustomerProductOrderItem may reference ServicOrderItems or ResourceOrderItems that participate in the Product required delivery.<br/><i>Relationships with ServicOrderItem, ResourceOrderItem are not shared with Business Partner orders.</i><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1220" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure C.03a - Customer Product Order Item Business Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1222> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1230> ;
    skos:definition "ShoppingCart looks like CustomerProductOrder except relationships with BillingAccount, Payment and SalesChannel that do not exit for ShoppingCart.<br/>In the same way ShoppingCartOfferingItem and ShoppingCartItem looks like CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem and<font color=\"#00ff7f\"> </font>CustomerProductOrderItem except elationships with BillingAccount and Payment that do not exit for ShoppingCartOfferingItem.<br/>It isn't mandatory to use ShoppingCart, CustomerProductOrder is enough to cover all the Customer Order Handling process. But some CSP might prefer to keep the view of what the customer decided to buy seperated from the final order. In this case, we can instantiate an instance of ShoppingCart and when the customer is identified, instantiate a CustomerOrder referring to the ShoppingCart.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1222" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure C.03b - Shopping Cart and Shopping Cart Item Business Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1224> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1230> ;
    skos:definition "A SalesOpportunity may lead to one or many SalesQuotes.<br/>A SalesQuote is a document that allows a Prospect to view the cost involved in purchasing specific Products. It is generally used by suppliers or resellers to begin a business transaction and specifies validity period for acceptance of the quote and possibly an authorisation process depending on the value of the quote.<br/>For specifying Products and ProductOfferingInstances proposed, their configuration and the related cost, the SalesQuote proposes one or many CustomerProductOrders.<br/>A SalesQuote might be described by a SalesQuoteSpecification. <br/>SalesQuoteSpecification is used to define the common characteristics (attributes, constraints and relationships) of a SalesQuote i.e. CSP would have a pre-defined template (specification) to generate the quote for different customer segments &/or products.<br/> - e.g. SalesQuote specification might be different depending on type of products. The quote specs for broadband products will differ from those for mobile.<br/> - e.g. the SaleQuote specification might be different depending on the size of enterprise lead. The quote generated for SOHO (Small Office Home Office) may be in a different format to that for an SME (Small and Medium sized Enterprises).<br/> - e.g. MPLS multi-protocol label switching. Though it is one overarching complex product it has multiple subtypes of products that should be included in the SalesQuote.<br/>Each SalesQuoteSpecification might be categorized by one or many SalesQuoteSpecificationType. <br/>To be able to propose a SalesQuote to the Prospect, it might need to be validated internaly by the CSP. This is tracked through a SalesQuoteAgreement and its related AgreementApproval.<br/>A SalesQuote might be represented by one or many Attachement such as a document that might be sent to the Prospect through an email. Several Attachements might be associated to the same SalesQuote for example if the validPeriod of the SalesQuote is updated, a new attachement is generated.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1224" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure C.03c - SalesQuote overview (copy of Figure SLO.03)"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1226> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1230> ;
    skos:definition "One or many PartyRoles might be involved in a CustomerProductOrder / CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem such as Distributor, Holder, Buyer or Product User.<br/>Each CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem requires an action (AllowedProductAction) on a ProductOfferingSpecification. It can involve one ProductOfferingInstance. In the specific case of ProductOfferingSpecificationMigration action, it will also involve the ProductOfferingInstance from which the migration is performed.<br/>The prices applicable are related to the ProductOfferingInstance (ProductPrice) or to ProductOfferingOrderItem when it corresponds to prices not specific to a ProductOfferingInstance such as a global 5% discount on ProductOrder one-time fees.<br/>A CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem may also specify the commitment chosen by the Customer (i.e. CommitmentTermOrCondition).<br/>The CustomerProductOfferingOrderItems may specify the CustomerBillingAccount to which the ProductOfferingInstances are charged to.<br/>When CustomerProductOfferingOrderItems are not charged to a CustomerBillingAccount and carry one-time charges, they might be directly paid through one or many CustomerPayments. The same CustomerPayment may concern several ProductPrices.<br/>CustomerProductOfferingOrderItem may reference CustomerProductOrderItems that participate in the ProductOfferingInstance required delivery.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1226" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure C.03d - Customer Product Offering Order Item Business Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1228> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1230> ;
    skos:definition "• Start : The initial state of a newly created SalesQuote, at this point the quote is not considered valid to be placed in front of the Prospect. <br/> • Internal Approval : If the Sales Quote does require an internal CSP approval process before to be placed in front of the Prospect. then it may be transitioned from New into Internal Approval to recognise the fact that the quote requires and is waiting for the approval process to complete. The business object for quote may contain a reference to the Approval business object that represents the management of this process. <br/> • In Progress : The quote is in progress state when the user saves a quote after it is created. This is the state after the Internal Approval state if required. <br/> • Approved : If the Sales Quote has been approved internally if required and also by the prospect/customer then it may be transitioned into the Approved state, which makes it valid with regard to placing in front of the Prospect for the final Quote journey. <br/> • Rejected : If the newly created Sales Quote is not required or if it is not deemed appropriate, may be as part of the approval process then it may be transitioned into the terminating state of Rejected. In this state it may not be recovered, instead a new quote would have to be created. <br/> • Expired : The quote expires if the quote expiry period is reached. The quote can be revived at this stage and moved to be in progress again. <br/> • Closed - Expired : The quote expires if the quote expiry period is reached and can not be revived after this stage. <br/> • Closed : The Prospect/Customer has been shown the quote and has decided to purchase the Products. The Sales Quote has therefore generated one or more CustomerProductOrders.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA4_EA2_EA1228" ;
    skos:prefLabel "SalesQuote Lifecycle"@en .

