<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1911> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1919> ;
    skos:definition "Put simply, usage is how much service is used, by whom is it used, where and when is it used and circumstances under which it is used. Normally, when a usage event occurs, it is stored in a network element, for instance in a switch, router, gateway or in an application system. Resources (applications, network and computing capabilities) usually store usage data in proprietary formats that are not understood by the billing system. Depending on the polling strategy, a mediation engine connects to resources, collects usage data and formats them into a format that is understood by the billing system. Output of a mediation engine are Usage Detail Records (UDRs). Examples of UDRs are Call Detail Records (CDRs – used to describe usage details of voice call services) and Internet Protocol Detail Records (IPDRs – used to describe usage details of Internet Protocol based services). In this document we will use the Usage abstract business entity to describe any resource-, service- or product-based usage that the billing system can read, update and process.<br/><br/>The following two Figures show business entities that are used to model usage. The model shown below is generic; particular usage models should define their own usage business entities by extending the Usage entity.<br/>The UsageSpecification class describes a type of usage. In order to achieve a flexible structure of the UsageSpecification all its attributes are stored as characteristics. Alternatively, different types of usage could be modelled as sub-classes of the Usage entities (Usage, ProductUsage, ServiceUsage, ResourceUsage).<br/>The UsageSpecification is comprised of UsageSpecCharacteristics that define all characteristics (attributes) known by a particular type of usage. Each characteristic is described by its name, category, presence and a set of allowed values.<br/>Name defines a unique name that identifies the characteristic.<br/>Category defines one of the high-level aspects of the usage information described by the characteristic. These categories are commonly referred to as: Who, When, What, Where, and Why.<br/>Presence defines whether the characteristic is required or optional.<br/>The set of allowed values is modelled with UsageSpecCharacteristicValue. This class describes all allowed values or value ranges.<br/>Additional information regarding the CharacteristicSpecification/CharactersticValue pattern can be found in GB922– Root Business Entities.<br/>The UsageSpecification entity has the following subclasses:<br/><ul><li>ServiceUsageSpec (that represents a service usage);</li><li>ResourceUsageSpec (that represents a resource usage);</li><li>ProductUsageSpec (that represents a product usage).</li></ul><p/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1911" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Pr.33 - Usage Specification"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1913> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1919> ;
    skos:definition "The Usage class represents a usage event. It is described by the UsageSpecification and comprised of UsageCharacteristicValues that hold data attributes of a usage specified by UsageSpecCharacteristics. The UsageCharacteristic can either store its value in the usageCharValue property or reference predefined UsageSpecCharacteristicValue.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1913" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Pr.34 - Usage"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1915> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1919> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">A Product is realized as one or more Service(s) and/or Resource(s). A Product is created by instantiating a ProductOfferingSpecification and adding it to a specific customer account. In order to charge a service (or a resource) usage, the service (or resource) has to be associated to a product.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The following Figure shows relationships among the ProductSpecification, the Product, the ProductUsageSpec and the ProductUsage ABEs. The ProductUsageSpec is defined for the certain ProductSpecification. As the ProductSpecification has 2 subclasses (the AtomicProductSpecification and the CompositeProductSpecification), the ProductUsageSpec needs 2 subclasses as well: the AtomicProductUsageSpec and the CompositeProductUsageSpec (associated with the AtomicProductSpecification and the CompositeProductSpecification entities respectively).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The ProductUsage describes the usage of an instantiated Product. The Product ABE is extended with the ProductComponent and the ProductBundle business entities. Consequently, the ProductUsage is extended with ProductComponentUsage and the ProductBundleUsage business entities (that are associated with the ProductComponent and the ProductBundle respectively).</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1915" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Pr.35 - Product Usage, Part 1"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1917> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1919> ;
    skos:definition "As mentioned above, a product is realized as one or more services and/or resources. Consequently, the ProductUsageSpec business entity has to be associated with the ResourceUsageSpec and the ServiceUsageSpec business entities. The ProductUsage, the ServiceUsage and the ResourceUsage business entities have to reflect these associations as well. The ProductComponentUsage can be associated with either ServiceUsage or ResourceUsage and included in a ProductBundleUsage. These entities and associations are shown on the following Figure.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1917" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Pr.36 - Product Usage, Part 2"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1_EA1922> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1_EA1924> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are the business entities aggregated under the <b>Product Usage Entity </b>Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1_EA1922" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure PrE.01 - Product Usage Entity ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1_EA1925> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1_EA1924> ;
    skos:definition "A detailed product bundle usage event, It is comprised of other ProductUsage(s), that may be either ProductBundleUsage(s) or ProductComponentUsage(s).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1_EA1925" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ProductBundleUsage"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1_EA1926> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1_EA1924> ;
    skos:definition "A detailed product component usage event.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1_EA1926" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ProductComponentUsage"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1_EA1927> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1_EA1924> ;
    skos:definition "An occurrence of employing a Product for its intended purpose.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA1_EA1927" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ProductUsage"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA2_EA1928> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA2_EA1930> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are the business entities aggregated under the <b>Product Usage Specification</b> Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA2_EA1928" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure PUS.01 - Product Usage Spec ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA2_EA1931> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA2_EA1930> ;
    skos:definition "A detailed description of the usage of a product, described by AtomicProductSpecification<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA2_EA1931" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AtomicProductUsageSpec"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA2_EA1932> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA2_EA1930> ;
    skos:definition "A detailed description of the usage of a Product, specified by CompositeProductSpecification. It is formed by aggregating other ProductUsageSpec(s), which may be either Composite or Atomic ProductUsageSpec(s) or Atomic ProductUsageSpec(s).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA2_EA1932" ;
    skos:prefLabel "CompositeProductUsageSpec"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA2_EA1933> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA2_EA1930> ;
    skos:definition "A detailed description of a product usage event. It represents customer's transaction as a whole or its autonomously billable part.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA6_EA2_EA1933" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ProductUsageSpec"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1934> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1948> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">A loyalty program is one of the tools used by the loyalty process to retain customers. For example, another tool is the ProductOfferingSpecification Commitment.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\"><br/></font><font color=\"#29313b\">An example of loyalty program could be « Change Your Mobile Offer »:</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">available only for prepaid contracts, therefore incompatible with postpaid contracts,</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">month after month the customer earns points and depending on the number of points he has, he can buy a new handset at a lower price using his points.</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">Another example could be a “more time for calls” program that gives you more time for calls according to your seniority (i.e.: 5% after six months of seniority, 10% after two years of seniority, etc.).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">And these two loyalty programs could have a cost and be incompatible.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The aim of marketing is to find levers in the form of rewards to enhance customer loyalty to its operator.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Most of the time, the conditions to reward a customer are based on </font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">seniority in customer relationship,</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">the importance of revenue from the customer,</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">or the risk of churn.</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">The more the customer remains with the operator or consumes, the more he will be rewarded.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\"><br/></font><font color=\"#29313b\">Different types of rewards can be considered:</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">physical rewards: accessories, terminals, points usable to buy accessories / terminals ...</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">virtual rewards: free usage, vouchers ...</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">The rewards that can be bought thanks to loyalty earns correspond to ProductSpecification & ProductOfferingSpecification with a price allowing a specific currency (loyalty points).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">A loyalty program is a part of a contract and may be either mandatory or not (packaging rule, pre-requisite).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">As a loyalty program represents a cost for the operator, the latter avoids that the customer may have several loyalty programs.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">To do so, Loyalty Programs might be incompatible with each other and in this case the customer has to choose only one LoyaltyProgram.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Therefore, a loyalty program is a type of AtomicProductSpecification, is packaged through ProductOfferingSpecification and is instantiated in the same manner in the installed base (LoyaltyProgramProduct that is a type of ProductComponent).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">A LoyaltyProgramProdSpec defines the LoyaltyRules that have to be checked in order to identify the actions to apply. A LoyaltyRule is a type of PolicyRule.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Depending on the type of LoyaltyRules a LoyaltyAccount might be needed to collect gains or not. This is defined by the needsLoyaltyAccount attribute on the LoyaltyProgramProdSpec entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1934" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Pr.37 - Loyalty Program main view"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1936> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1948> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Here after, an illustration of the Figure Pr.37 - Loyalty Program main view via a loyalty program to change handset.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The Mobile contract contains:</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">a ProductOfferingSpecification for the Mobile Line,</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">and a loyalty ProductOfferingSpecification “Change Your Mobile”.</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">The loyalty ProductOfferingSpecification “Change Your Mobile” packages a LoyaltyProgramProdSpec that enables to earn points that can be burnt to buy a new handset.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Therefore, the LoyaltyProgramProdSpec defines two rules</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">one to reward consumption,</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">and a second one to interest young people.</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">As John Smith has ordered a Mobile contract he has the corresponding installed base elements including the “JS’s CYM by loyalty” LoyaltyProduct.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">As John Smith has no LoyaltyAccount, “JS LoyaltyAccount” is created to collect the earns gained thanks to his “JS’s CYM by Loyalty” LoyaltyProgramProduct.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1936" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Pr.37-I01 - Loyalty Program main view"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1938> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1948> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">A LoyaltyRule specifies:</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">Events triggering the evaluation of the rule (LoyaltyEvent)</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\"> • Ex: Every first of a month, a CustomerOrder of Top-Up</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">Conditions that have to be checked (LoyaltyCondition)</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\"> • Ex: If the invoice amount is above 100 €, If more than 2 hours of international call</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">Actions that should be performed if the condition clause is evaluated to TRUE (LoyaltyAction)</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\"> • Ex: Give 50 SMS free, Credit 10 points on the LoyaltyAccount</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\"><br/></font><font color=\"#29313b\">Loyalty Rules may result in</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">either rewards directly used / usable by the customer</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\"> • Ex: 5% more time on the communications package after 6 months of age, and 10% after one year ...</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">or loyalty earn that are gathered on an account to be used to pay later a ProductOfferingSpecification</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\"> • Ex: 400 points to welcome a subscription then 10 points for every Euro charged. The points collected can be used to buy rewards like a USB stick, 100 SMS…</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The different types of LoyaltyEvent may be event that occurs on BillingAccount (Ex: amount of Invoice, recurring charge), on PartyRole (Ex: CustomerOrder amount), on Products (Ex: monthly international usage volume).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">A LoyaltyAction may correspond either to a CustomerOrder (Ex: 100 SMS free), or to an Interaction (Ex: a SMS notifying the 100 SMS free) or to a LoyaltyEarn (Ex: 100 points on the LoyaltyAccount)</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Each time a LoyaltyEvent happens, LoyaltyConditions from LoyaltyRules triggered by this type of event are evaluated. </font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">If the result is true, a LoyaltyExecutionPoint is noted tracking the application of the rule and triggering BusinessInteraction, CustomerOrder or LoyaltyEarn. A LoyaltyExecutionPoint is a type of PolicyExecutionPoint.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\"><br/></font><font color=\"#29313b\">Depending on event’s type used in LoyaltyRule, the LoyaltyProgramProduct will specify entities from which it computes events (BillingAccount, Product…). The way to specify these boundaries from which loyalty events are collected to calculate the gains is not yet represented in this diagram and needs to be further studied.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1938" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Pr.38 - Loyalty Rule"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1940> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1948> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Here after, an illustration of the Figure Pr.38 - Loyalty Rule via a focus on the loyalty program to change handset.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\"><br/></font><font color=\"#29313b\">The “Consuming advantage” LoyaltyRule consists in:</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">evaluation for each Invoice</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">only if the amount is higher than 10€</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">apply a LoyaltyEarn based on the total amount of the Invoice</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">The « Advantage for young people » LoyaltyRule consists in:</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">evaluation each 1st January</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">only if the customer is younger than 26 years old </font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">apply a LoyaltyEarn as a result</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\"><br/></font><font color=\"#29313b\">As John Smith’s Mobile contract has been invoiced, an event is collected.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">As the amount is higher than 10€, the LoyaltyAction is triggered and corresponds to a LoyaltyEarn of 70 points (50 + 20).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\"><br/></font><font color=\"#29313b\">The 1st of January, the « Advantage for young people » rule is evaluated, but unfortunately John Smith is older than 26 years, so he gets no Loyalty Earn.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1940" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Pr.38-I01 - Loyalty Rule"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1942> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1948> ;
    skos:definition "A LoyaltyAccount corresponds to a set of balances to carry loyalty movement according to different valid period and unit.<br/>A LoyaltyAccount may be required to realize a LoyaltyProgramProduct according to the rules carried by the corresponding LoyaltyProgramProdSpec.<br/>A LoyaltyAccount may collect results from one or more LoyaltyProgramProduct.<br/>A LoyaltyProgramMember is defined on each LoyaltyAccount. A LoyaltyProgramMember is a type of PartyRole and is granted with the rights on the LoyaltyAccount such as to execute LoyaltyBurn used to realize a CustomerPayment.<br/>Each LoyaltyBalance gathers LoyaltyEarns and LoyaltyBurns.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1942" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Pr.39 - Loyalty Account"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1944> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1948> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Here after, an illustration of the Figure Pr.39 - Loyalty Account via a focus on the application of the loyalty program to change handset.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\"><br/></font><font color=\"#29313b\">The LoyaltyEarn is gathered into the LoyaltyBalance of JS LoyaltyAccount.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Mary Smith is declared as the LoyaltyProgramMember of the LoyaltyAccount.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Therefore, she can use the gains collected on it (LoyaltyEarns).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">She buys a new handset with part of the payment done with 50 loyalty points corresponding to 5€. So she executes a LoyaltyBurn to pay it.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1944" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Pr.39-I01 - Loyalty Account"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1946> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1948> ;
    skos:definition "The means of payment is classified by PaymentMethod.<br/>For example, payment by cash, check, bank card (credit card or debit card), third party (like bank transfer, payment tool), account balance and loyalty burn. <br/>The LoyaltyBurnPM is a type of PaymentMethod that uses a LoyaltyAccount.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1946" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Pr.40a - Payment Method and Plan"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1949> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1948> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Here after, an illustration of the Figure Pr.37 - Loyalty Program main view via a loyalty program to change handset.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The Mobile contract contains:</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">a ProductOffering for the Mobile Line,</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">and a loyalty ProductOffering “Change Your Mobile”.</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">The loyalty ProductOffering “Change Your Mobile” packages a LoyaltyProgramProdSpec that enables to earn points that can be burnt to buy a new handset.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Therefore, the LoyaltyProgramProdSpec defines two rules</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">one to reward consumption,</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">and a second one to interest young people.</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">As John Smith has ordered a Mobile contract he has the corresponding installed base elements including the “JS’s CYM by loyalty” LoyaltyProduct.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">As John Smith has no LoyaltyAccount, “JS LoyaltyAccount” is created to collect the earns gained thanks to his “JS’s CYM by Loyalty” LoyaltyProgramProduct.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1949" ;
    skos:prefLabel "EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1949"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1950> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1948> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1950" ;
    skos:prefLabel "EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1950"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1951> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1948> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Here after, an illustration of the Figure Pr.39 - Loyalty Account via a focus on the application of the loyalty program to change handset.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\"><br/></font><font color=\"#29313b\">The LoyaltyEarn is gathered into the LoyaltyBalance of JS LoyaltyAccount.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Mary Smith is declared as the LoyaltyProgramMember of the LoyaltyAccount.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Therefore, she can use the gains collected on it (LoyaltyEarns).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">She buys a new handset with part of the payment done with 50 loyalty points corresponding to 5€. So she executes a LoyaltyBurn to pay it.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1951" ;
    skos:prefLabel "EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1951"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1954> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1956> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are the business entities aggregated under the <b>Loyalty Program </b>Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1954" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure LP.01 - Loyalty Program ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1957> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1956> ;
    skos:definition "A LoyaltyAccount corresponds to a set of balances to carry loyalty movement according to different valid period and unit.<br/><br/>A LoyaltyAccount may be required to realize a LoyaltyProgramProduct according to the rules carried by the corresponding LoyaltyProgramProdSpec. This is defined by the needsLoyaltyAccount attribute on the LoyaltyProgramProdSpec entity.<br/><br/>A LoyaltyAccount may collect results from one or more LoyaltyProgramProduct.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1957" ;
    skos:prefLabel "LoyaltyAccount"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1958> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1956> ;
    skos:definition "A LoyaltyBalance is credited by LoyaltyEarns and debited by LoyaltyBurns.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1958" ;
    skos:prefLabel "LoyaltyBalance"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1959> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1956> ;
    skos:definition "A LoyaltyBurn represents the use of a certain quantity on a LoyaltyBalance. It is used to be gathered into a CustomerPayment.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1959" ;
    skos:prefLabel "LoyaltyBurn"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1960> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1956> ;
    skos:definition "A LoyaltyEarn represents a gain credited on a LoyaltyBalance.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1960" ;
    skos:prefLabel "LoyaltyEarn"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1961> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1956> ;
    skos:definition "A LoyaltyExecutionPoint is a type of PolicyExecutionPoint.<br/><br/>A LoyaltyExecutionPoint tracks the application of a LoyaltyAction and may trigger BusinessInteraction, CustomerProductOrder or LoyaltyEarn.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1961" ;
    skos:prefLabel "LoyaltyExecutionPoint"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1962> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1956> ;
    skos:definition "A LoyaltyProgramMember is defined on each LoyaltyAccount. A LoyaltyProgramMember is a type of PartyRole and is granted with the rights on the LoyaltyAccount such as to execute LoyaltyBurn used to realize a CustomerPayment.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1962" ;
    skos:prefLabel "LoyaltyProgramMember"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1963> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1956> ;
    skos:definition "A LoyaltyProgramProduct is a type of ProductComponent.<br/><br/>It is described by a LoyaltyProgramProdSpec.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA1_EA1963" ;
    skos:prefLabel "LoyaltyProgramProduct"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1964> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1966> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are the business entities aggregated under the <b>Loyalty Program Specification</b> Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1964" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure LPS.01 - Loyalty Program Specification ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1967> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1966> ;
    skos:definition "A LoyaltyAction may correspond either to a CustomerProductOrder (Ex: 100 SMS free), or to an Interaction (Ex: a SMS notifying the 100 SMS free) or to a LoyaltyEarn (Ex: 100 points on the LoyaltyAccount)<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1967" ;
    skos:prefLabel "LoyaltyAction"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1968> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1966> ;
    skos:definition "A LoyaltyCondition specifies the condition that has to be evaluated to decide if the LoyaltyAction(s) from the LoyaltyRule have to be done.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1968" ;
    skos:prefLabel "LoyaltyCondition"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1969> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1966> ;
    skos:definition "The different types of LoyaltyEvent may be event that occurs on BillingAccount (Ex: amount of Invoice, recurring charge), on PartyRole (Ex: CustomerProductOrder amount), on Products (Ex: monthly international usage volume).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1969" ;
    skos:prefLabel "LoyaltyEvent"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1970> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1966> ;
    skos:definition "A LoyaltyProgramProdSpec is a type of AtomicProductSpecification, is packaged through ProductOffering and is instantiated in the same manner in the installed base (LoyaltyProgramProduct that is a type of ProductComponent).<br/><br/>A LoyaltyProgramProdSpec defines one or more LoyaltyRules that have to be checked in order to identify the actions to apply.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1970" ;
    skos:prefLabel "LoyaltyProgramProdSpec"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1971> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1966> ;
    skos:definition "A LoyaltyRule is a type of PolicyRule defined by a LoyaltyProgramProdSpec.<br/><br/>A LoyaltyRule specifies:<br/><br/>• Events triggering the evaluation of the rule (LoyaltyEvent)<br/><br/> o Ex: Every first of a month, a CustomerProductOrder of Top-Up<br/><br/>• Conditions that have to be checked (LoyaltyCondition)<br/><br/> o Ex: If the invoice amount is above 100 €, If more than 2 hours of international call<br/><br/>• Actions that should be performed if the condition clause is evaluated to TRUE (LoyaltyAction)<br/><br/> o Ex: Give 50 SMS free, Credit 10 points on the LoyaltyAccount<br/><br/><br/><br/>Loyalty Rules may result in<br/><br/>• either rewards directly used / usable by the customer<br/><br/> o Ex: 5% more time on the communications package after 6 months of age, and 10% after one year ...<br/><br/>• or loyalty earn that are gathered on an account to be used to pay later a ProductOffering<br/><br/> o Ex: 400 points to welcome a subscription then 10 points for every Euro charged. The points collected can be used to buy rewards like a USB stick, 100 SMS…<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA7_EA2_EA1971" ;
    skos:prefLabel "LoyaltyRule"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1972> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1974> ;
    skos:definition "A Configuration (also referred to as a Profile) defines how a Resource, Service, or Product operates or functions. A Configuration may contain one or more parts (which is realized by using the Atomic/Composite pattern, but it is represented as a single entity - ConfigurationRelationship), and each part may contain zero or more fields. Each field may have attributes that are statically or dynamically defined. Some of these fields have fixed values, while others provide values from which a choice or choices can be made (e.g., using the EntitySpec/Entity and/or CharacteristicSpec/CharacteristicValue patterns).<br/>Starting from the right-side of the figure:<br/><ul><li>The Resource, Service and Product classes are as defined in the SID model. </li><li>The associated configuration objects are used to define additional properties (attributes) of the associated entity. For example, consider an Equipment instance (a Resource). The intrinsic properties of the Equipment instance (perhaps but not necessarily common to all Equipment instances) are defined in the Resource itself. Additional properties (which may not be common to all Equipment instances) are provided in one or one Resource Configuration instances. </li></ul><ul><li>It is possible to relate one instance of Configuration to several others via the ConfigRelationship. This is useful when configuring complex (aggregate) entities. For example, to configure a circuit pack, one may also need to configure the various ports supported by the circuit pack and in turn, the connection termination points supported by the ports. </li></ul>On the left-side of the figure, there are various Configuration Specifications that correspond to the various Configuration classes on the right-side of the figure. This is the typical EntitySpecification/Entity pattern already present in the SID model but now applied to a particular kind of Entity, i.e., a Configuration. The EntitySpecification represents the definition of an entity. The idea is that the various ResourceConfigSpec instances are reusable across many instances of Resource.<br/><i>Refer to Common Domain guide book section Configuration and Profile ABE for more details</i><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1972" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure CP.01 - Configuration Spec and Configuration (copy from Common)"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1975> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1974> ;
    skos:definition "A Configuration (also referred to as a Profile) defines how a Resource, Service, or Product operates or functions. A Configuration may contain one or more parts (which is realized by using the Atomic/Composite pattern, but it is represented as a single entity - ConfigurationRelationship), and each part may contain zero or more fields. Each field may have attributes that are statically or dynamically defined. Some of these fields have fixed values, while others provide values from which a choice or choices can be made (e.g., using the EntitySpec/Entity and/or CharacteristicSpec/CharacteristicValue patterns).<br/>Starting from the right-side of the figure:<br/><ul><li>The Resource, Service and Product classes are as defined in the SID model. </li></ul><ul><li>The associated configuration objects are used to define additional properties (attributes) of the associated entity. For example, consider an Equipment instance (a Resource). The intrinsic properties of the Equipment instance (perhaps but not necessarily common to all Equipment instances) are defined in the Resource itself. Additional properties (which may not be common to all Equipment instances) are provided in one or one Resource Configuration instances. </li></ul><ul><li>It is possible to relate one instance of Configuration to several others via the ConfigRelationship. This is useful when configuring complex (aggregate) entities. For example, to configure a circuit pack, one may also need to configure the various ports supported by the circuit pack and in turn, the connection termination points supported by the ports. </li></ul>On the left-side of the figure, there are various Configuration Specifications that correspond to the various Configuration classes on the right-side of the figure. This is the typical EntitySpecification/Entity pattern already present in the SID model but now applied to a particular kind of Entity, i.e., a Configuration. The EntitySpecification represents the definition of an entity. The idea is that the various ResourceConfigSpec instances are reusable across many instances of Resource.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1975" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure CP.01 - Configuration Spec and Configuration"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1976> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1974> ;
    skos:definition "The definition of how a Product operates or functions in terms of CharacteristicSpecification(s) and related ResourceSpec(s), ProductSpec(s), ServiceSpec(s).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1976" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ProductConfigSpec"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1977> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1974> ;
    skos:definition "A representation of how a Product operates or functions in terms of characteristics and related Resource(s), Product(s), Service(s).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1977" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ProductConfiguration"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1979> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1987> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are the business entities aggregated under the <b>Product Action</b> Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1979" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure PA.01 - Product Action ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1981> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1987> ;
    skos:definition "This diagram shows two AllowedProductAction specializations. ProductOfferingSpecificationMigration is a type of AllowedProductAction used to specify which migration action (or move) from one source ProductOfferingSpecification to one or several destination ProductOfferingSpecification can be performed.<br/>ProductOfferingSpecificationMerge is a type of AllowedProductAction used to specify which merge action from a minimum of two source ProductOfferingSpecification to a unique destination ProductOfferingSpecification can be performed.<br/><br/>Note: This diagram does not represent all possible subclasses of AllowedProductAction. Others could be added.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1981" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure PA.02 - ProductOfferingSpecificationMigration and ProductOfferingSpecificationMerge"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1983> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1987> ;
    skos:definition "This illustration provides examples of instantiation of ProductOfferingSpecificationMigration BE.<br/>A \"Low Cost Offer Migration\" instance of ProductOfferingSpecificationMigration defines that it is possible to migrate:<br/>- From \"Low Cost Mobile Offer\",<br/>- To \"Standard Mobile Offer\" or \"Premium Mobile Offer\".<br/><br/>A \"Standard Offer Migration\" instance of ProductOfferingSpecificationMigration defines that it is possible to migrate:<br/>- From \"Standard Mobile Offer\",<br/>- To \"Premium Mobile Offer\".<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1983" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure PA.02.I01 - ProductOfferingSpecificationMigration example"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1985> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1987> ;
    skos:definition "This illustration provides an example of instantiation of ProductOfferingSpecificationMerge BE.<br/>A \"Quad Play Offer Merge\" instance of ProductOfferingSpecificationMerge defines that it is possible to merge:<br/>- a \"Standard Mobile Offer\" and a \"Triple Play (Internet, Fixed line, TV) Offer\",<br/>- To a \"Quadruple Play (Mobile, Internet, Fixed line, TV) Offer\".<br/><br/>A \"Standard Offer Migration\" instance of ProductOfferingSpecificationMigration defines that it is possible to migrate:<br/>- From \"Standard Mobile Offer\",<br/>- To \"Premium Mobile Offer\".<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1985" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure PA.02.I02 ProductOfferingSpecificationMerge example"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1988> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1987> ;
    skos:definition "Idea here is to model the migration of an offer to another offer<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA5_EA8_EA1_EA1988" ;
