<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2781> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2797> ;
    skos:definition "The following Figure shows the details of the corresponding Software Specification classes.<br/>SoftwareResourceSpecification in the figure depicts the attributes that are shared by every instance of an associated SoftwareResource entity.<br/>The SoftwareSpecification entity has been shown separately from the APISpecification entity because it contains attributes unique to it as shown in the figure. For an example of APISpecification entity usage please refer to Root Guidebook.<br/>The composite/atomic pattern has been applied to the SoftwareSpecification entity to allow for groupings of Software, such as the software module specifications that are contained within an application specification. Note that the application specification is not shown as a subclass of SoftwareSpecification. This is because there have been no unique attributes discovered for it.<br/><i>Note that there are many attributes and associations inherited by SoftwareResourceSpecification, such as the association to SupplierPartner from ResourceSpecification as well as others from LogicalResourceSpecification (Refer to the corresponding section).</i><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2781" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure ResCS.01 - Software Resource Specification"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2783> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2797> ;
    skos:definition "There can be many types of relationships that exist among SoftwareResourceSpecifications. These are shown in the Figure below.<br/>The SoftwareResourceSpecRelationship entity has purposely been made non-abstract so that new types of simple relationships can be defined in addition to those shown. If base set of attributes in it are not sufficient then new subclasses can be explicitly modelled or the Characteristic pattern can be used to dynamically add the attributes to a new type.<br/>The SoftwareSpecRefinementRelationship subclass defines divisions of a SoftwareResourceSpecification into two or more other specifications. Or fusions of two or more specifications into a single specification. Or one specification can be substituted for another. <br/>The SoftwareSpecConstraintRelationship subclass allows additional constraints to be defined for involved specification. The SymmetricConstraint attribute of this subclass is used indicate if the relationship is from the perspective of just one specification or from both for example, A constrains B, and B constrains A.<br/>The SoftwareSpecAlternativeRelationship subclass defines specifications that are alternates of others. Its attributes indicate if the alternate is an exact alternate. The symmetric attribute indicates whether A is an alternate for B and B is an alternate for A, or A is an alternate for B only.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2783" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure ResCS.02 - Software Resource Specification Relationship"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2785> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2797> ;
    skos:definition "The Figure below shows the relationships between specifications and entities.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2785" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure ResCS.03 - Software Resource Specification Subclass and Their Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2787> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2797> ;
    skos:definition "The Figure below shows associations between SoftwareSpecification, CompoundResourceSpec, and ResourceSpecification.<br/>The first simple association is used to specify that a CompoundResourceSpecification may be realized by SoftwareSpecification alone and not a combination of at least one PhysicalResourceSpec and at least one LogicalResourceSpec. This changes the definition of a CompoundResourceSpec and a CompoundResource that will be shown in an upcoming figure.<br/>The association class is used to show the status of a SoftwareSpecification that can run on any ResourceSpecification. For example, the status may reflect that it can or can no longer be run. The association was made so that any type of resource (within reason!) could run Software, such as a CompoundResource, LogicalDevice or PhysicalDevice.<br/>The SoftwareSpecificationUses association was added so that any type of Software could use any type of Resource (again, within reason). For example, Software could use memory (logical or physical), memory databases, or physical disks of any type.<br/>HostingPlatformRequirementSpec has been introduced to represent the requirements that must be fulfilled by the platform on which the InstalledSoftware will run (e.g. compute, storage, network).<br/>The derived association “/SoftwareSpecificatonRequires” is used to document the requirements necessary to a platform to be capable of hosting the concerned software before it is installed.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2787" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure ResCS.04 - Software Specification and Resource Specification"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2789> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2797> ;
    skos:definition "The Figure below shows the associations between SoftwareResource and PartyRole.<br/>One association deals with the licensing of a SoftwareResource by Parties playing a PartyRole. The other association deals with the use of a SoftwareResource.<br/>The figure also shows the attributes that are common to APIs and InstalledSoftware.<br/><i>Note that there are many attributes and associations inherited by SoftwareResource, such as the association to ResourceUsage from Resource as well as others inherited from LogicalResource (Refer to correspoding section).</i><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2789" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure ResCS.05 - Software Resource"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2791> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2797> ;
    skos:definition "A RunningSoftwareStatistic entity has also been introduced as shown in the Figure below.<br/>RunningSoftwareStatistic represents the characteristics of the running software, such as memory, physical disk, and CPU used. The characteristics are represented by the generalized attribute resourceUse with the type of use represented by the instance of Resource used. The useDateTime attribute records when the Resource is being or has been used.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2791" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure ResCS.07 - Running Software Statistic"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2793> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2797> ;
    skos:definition "As mentioned earlier, a number of associations have been enhanced and added to support the requirements of today’s digital world. This section describes them.<br/>The Figure below shows one group of associations that were added/enhanced.<br/>The association between ResourceElement and InstalledSoftware deserves a few comments. First, the association may appear to be redundant, because a CompoundResource is composed of Logical, Physical, and Compound Resources. However, since ResourceElements can be realized purely by Software, this fact was deemed important enough to justify adding a direct association between the two entities. Second, Figure CS.04 – Software Specification and Resource Specification shows a similar association between CompoundResourceSpecification and SoftwareSpecification. The reason for the difference is that there is no ResourceElementSpecification entity.<br/>The InstalledSoftwareRuns (InstalledSoftware) association has been added to support scenarios such as an operating system running desktop software or a virtual machine operating system running a java virtual machine operating system.<br/>The addition of the association between Supplier and ResourceSpecification was mentioned in a previous section of this document. It is shown here.<br/>The addition of the ResourceReferences association class was added to parallel the recursive association between ResourceSpecifications. It enables one Resource to reference another for a variety of reasons, such as one Resource replacing or being an alternate of another or to model a hierarchy of Resources.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2793" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure ResCS.08 - Model Association Enhancements - 1"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2795> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2797> ;
    skos:definition "One final entity and an association were added to support virtual memory as shown in the following Figure.<br/>In the figure VirtualMemory is shown to be related via inheritance to a PhysicalResource. However, it comes from the newly introduced ResourceRelationship and its two relationships with Resource.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA2_EA2795" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure ResCS.10 - Model Enhancements - Virtual Memory"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2858> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2860> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are the business entities aggregated under the <b>Address </b>Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2858" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Add.01 - Address ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2861> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2860> ;
    skos:definition "This class represents an IP address. It can be either in v4 or v6 form, and can be formatted as dotted decimal or CIDR. One or more host aliases can also be supplied.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2861" ;
    skos:prefLabel "IPAddress"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2862> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2860> ;
    skos:definition "This class refines the generic IP Address class to add formatting capabilities that are specific to IPv4.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2862" ;
    skos:prefLabel "IPv4Address"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2863> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2860> ;
    skos:definition "This class represents the generic concept of a network address. Its subclasses define different types of addresses of different technologies, such as an IPAddress vs. an IPXAddress. Its utility lies in its ability to serve as a convenient point for sourcing and terminating relationships. This eliminates undue duplication of relationships that interact with the subclasses of NetworkAddress.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2863" ;
    skos:prefLabel "NetworkAddress"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2864> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2860> ;
    skos:definition "The invariant characteristics that define a NetworkAddress. NetworkAddressSpecifications define different types of addresses of different technologies, such as an IPAddress vs. an IPXAddress. Each related NetworkAddress instance will have the same invariant characteristics. However, the values associated with other characteristics of the instantiated NetworkAddress entity are specific to each instance.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2864" ;
    skos:prefLabel "NetworkAddressSpecification"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2865> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2860> ;
    skos:definition "ISUP Signaling OPC and DPC attributes that map to Region, Subregion, Node Type, and Node Name.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA1_EA2865" ;
    skos:prefLabel "PointCode"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2839> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2841> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are the business entities aggregated under the <b>Logical Resource </b>Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2839" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure LR.01 - Logical Resource ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2845> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2841> ;
    skos:definition "A ConnectionPoint implements a ConnectionPointSpec.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2845" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ConnectionPoint"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2846> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2841> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2846" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Converged Network ABE"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2847> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2841> ;
    skos:definition "This is an abstract base class for describing different logical aspects of devices (e.g., DeviceInterfaces) that constitute a Product. It has two main purposes: (1) to collect common attributes and relationships for all logical entities, and (2) to provide a convenient, single point where relationships with other managed objects can be defined.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2847" ;
    skos:prefLabel "LogicalResource"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2849> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2841> ;
    skos:definition "This class defines the concept of various types of roles that can be associated with LogicalResources and LogicalResourceSpecs.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2849" ;
    skos:prefLabel "LogicalResourceRole"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2852> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2841> ;
    skos:definition "This class is used to define a set of ManagedPhysicalEntities that must be replaced as a unit. This is conceptually a set of FRUs.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2852" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ReplacementSet"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2854> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2841> ;
    skos:definition "A ResourceFunction is described by a ResourceFunctionSpec specifying the possible configurations.<br/><br/>A ResourceFunction is a function to transform inputs of any nature into outputs of any nature independently from the way it is provided. <br/><br/>Each time a ResourceFunctionSpecification is provided whatever the way it is done (SoftwareSpecification, SoftBlackBoxSpec or PhysicalBlackBox), a ResourceFunction is created with its ConnectionPoints.<br/><br/>The ResourceFunction is provided either by an InstalledSoftware, a SoftBlackBox, or a PhysicalBlackBox. These relationships are exclusive.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2854" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ResourceFunction"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2855> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2841> ;
    skos:definition "This class defines the semantics of the ResourceRolesManagedByPartyRole association.<br/><br/>The ResourceRolesManagedByPartyRole association defines the set of ResourceRoles that are managed by a particular PartyRole. Oftentimes, there are important functional differences between different types of Resources that require very different skill sets, methods, and so forth to be used by the PartyRole that is managing that Resource. For example, different management personnel may be assigned to manage core routers compared to edge routers. This applies not just to the router as a whole, but to its physical (e.g., line cards) and logical (e.g., DeviceInterfaces) components as well. This class captures these semantics.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2855" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ResourceRolePartyRoleDetails"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2866> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2870> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are the business entities aggregated under the <b>AI Model </b>Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">See <b>Ai Mode Specification </b>ABE for additional details.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2866" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure AiM.01 - Ai Model ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2868> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2870> ;
    skos:definition "The AI model lifecycle encapsulates a series of stages that guide the design, development, deployment, and maintenance of artificial intelligence models and supported systems. This lifecycle can be visualized as a state machine, where each state represents a distinct phase in the AI model's journey. Below is an exhaustive outline of this lifecycle, detailing each phase and its significance. The AI model lifecycle is not merely linear; it is iterative and interconnected. Each phase influences subsequent stages, necessitating continuous feedback loops for optimization. The lifecycle equips developers and organizations to build robust AI solutions that are secure, effective, and aligned with strategic goals.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2868" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure AiM.02 - AI Model Lifecycle"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2872> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2870> ;
    skos:definition "Subclass of CharacteristicValue. Represents the characteristics of the AiModel defined using AiModelSpecCharactieristic.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2872" ;
    skos:prefLabel "AIModelCharacteristicValue"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2873> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2871> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2873" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Archived"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2875> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2871> ;
    skos:definition "The process of gathering raw data from various sources relevant to the problem the AI model aims to solve.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2875" ;
    skos:prefLabel "DataCollection"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2876> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2871> ;
    skos:definition "The stage where collected data is cleaned, transformed, and organized (including training, and validation data separation) to be used for training the AI model.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2876" ;
    skos:prefLabel "DataPreparation"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2877> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2871> ;
    skos:definition "In this state, the model is integrated into a real-world application, and is being used. This state can have further sub-states that include Integration into Production: Deploy the trained model into a production environment where it can process real-time data. API Development: Create application programming interfaces (APIs) for seamless interaction with other systems or applications.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2877" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Deployed"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2879> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2871> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2879" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Final"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2880> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2871> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2880" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Final"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2881> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2871> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2881" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Initial"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2882> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2871> ;
    skos:definition "The model instance is created and initialized for onward preprocessing (not yet trained). This state includes further sub-stages that encompass problem definition, data aquisition and preparation and feature engineering etc.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2882" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Initialized"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2889> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2886> ;
    skos:definition "Done<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2889" ;
    skos:prefLabel "EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2889"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2890> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA3_EA3_EA2_EA2886> ;
    skos:definition "The AI model's training has encountered an Error<br/>"@en ;
