<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA4_EA3201> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA4_EA3203> ;
    skos:definition "A Configuration (also referred to as a Profile) defines how a Resource, Service, or Product operates or functions. A Configuration may contain one or more parts (which is realized by using the Atomic/Composite pattern, but it is represented as a single entity - ConfigurationRelationship), and each part may contain zero or more fields. Each field may have attributes that are statically or dynamically defined. Some of these fields have fixed values, while others provide values from which a choice or choices can be made (e.g., using the EntitySpec/Entity and/or CharacteristicSpec/CharacteristicValue patterns).<br/>Starting from the right-side of the figure:<br/> • The Resource, Service and Product classes are as defined in the SID model. <br/> • The associated configuration objects are used to define additional properties (attributes) of the associated entity. For example, consider an Equipment instance (a Resource). The intrinsic properties of the Equipment instance (perhaps but not necessarily common to all Equipment instances) are defined in the Resource itself. Additional properties (which may not be common to all Equipment instances) are provided in one or one Resource Configuration instances. <br/> • It is possible to relate one instance of Configuration to several others via the ConfigRelationship. This is useful when configuring complex (aggregate) entities. For example, to configure a circuit pack, one may also need to configure the various ports supported by the circuit pack and in turn, the connection termination points supported by the ports. <br/>On the left-side of the figure, there are various Configuration Specifications that correspond to the various Configuration classes on the right-side of the figure. This is the typical EntitySpecification/Entity pattern already present in the SID model but now applied to a particular kind of Entity, i.e., a Configuration. The EntitySpecification represents the definition of an entity. The idea is that the various ResourceConfigSpec instances are reusable across many instances of Resource.<br/><i>Refer to Common Domain guide book section Configuration and Profile ABE for more details</i><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA4_EA3201" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure CP.01 - Configuration Spec and Configuration (copy from Common)"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA4_EA3204> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA4_EA3203> ;
    skos:definition "The definition of how a Resource operates or functions in terms of CharacteristicSpecification(s) and related ResourceSpec(s).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA4_EA3204" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ResourceConfigSpec"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA4_EA3205> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA4_EA3203> ;
    skos:definition "A representation of how a Resource operates or functions in terms of characteristics and related Resource(s).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA4_EA3205" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ResourceConfiguration"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3225> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3227> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are the business entities aggregated under the <b>Resource Number Portability </b>Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3225" ;
    skos:prefLabel "RNP.01 - Resource Number Portability ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3228> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3227> ;
    skos:definition "This is a sub-class of PolicyRule in order to obtain the conditions, events and actions, which help especially for the penalty fees when certain conditions don't apply. The policies' approach is to only be applied and be considered for the number portability itself, depending of the type of the request based on the BusinessInteractionType.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3228" ;
    skos:prefLabel "NumberPortabilityPolicyRule"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3229> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3227> ;
    skos:definition "This is the main entity of the diagram (figure) for number portability and a concrete base class formed with NumberPortInRequest, NumberPortOutRequest, NumberPortOverRequest and NumberRetirementRequest. It has the attributes: ID (inherited), name, description (inherited), version, status (inherited), source, ProgramDate and telephonyType. The attribute version exist to manage all kinds of different versions during the whole lifecycle of the portability. This is precisely for cases like; if a client has an instance of a new number portability, exist a following or a trace. This can be approach through versioning. This can happen easily because the portability is associated with rules, many policies can apply for a certain period of time and change over time too, and may not belong necessarily to the same version. The attribute Source is applied to PortOver and Retirement, because they don’t have a direct relationship with other domains, they go straight directly through other sources. NPT needs a list of numbers to port over or to retire, and a source, that could be external or from any other origin. And last, Port In and Port Out need a program date (hence the attribute) to port, they both have a relationship with other domains, since they are issued by a customer order. The status attribute allows to see the availability of the request. It also considers the type of telephony for numbers for the portability, like mobile, fixed and IP numbers related to the request through the attribute TelephonyType.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3229" ;
    skos:prefLabel "NumberPortabilityRequest"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3230> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3227> ;
    skos:definition "This is a sub-class of NumberPortabilityRequest for describing and store the requests related to port in issued by customer orders.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3230" ;
    skos:prefLabel "NumberPortInRequest"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3231> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3227> ;
    skos:definition "This is a sub-class of NumberPortabilityRequest for describing and store the requests related to port out issued by a third CSP (Customer Service Provider).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3231" ;
    skos:prefLabel "NumberPortOutRequest"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3232> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3227> ;
    skos:definition "This is a sub-class of NumberPortabilityRequest for describing and store the requests related to port over and notifications between third CSPs (Customer Service Providers)<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3232" ;
    skos:prefLabel "NumberPortOverRequest"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3233> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3227> ;
    skos:definition "This is a sub-class of NumberPortabilityRequest for describing and store the requests related to retirement of numbers. This allows to send back telephone numbers that were previously ported in, and receive telephone numbers that were previously ported out.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3233" ;
    skos:prefLabel "NumberRetirementRequest"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3234> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3227> ;
    skos:definition "PortabilityRequestPolicyRule is the associated Class for the relationship of many-to-many between NumberPortabilityRequest and NumberPortabilityPolicyRule. Through this class, the relation combined of the both of them is stored.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA1_EA3234" ;
    skos:prefLabel "PortabilityRequestPolicyRule"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA2_EA3235> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA2_EA3237> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are the business entities aggregated under the <b>Resoure Number Portability Role </b>Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA2_EA3235" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure RNPR.01 - Resource Number Portability Role ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA2_EA3238> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA2_EA3237> ;
    skos:definition "Sub-class of PartyRole. It's the administrator of all number portability and the main center point for all the messages sent.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA2_EA3238" ;
    skos:prefLabel "NumberPortabilityClearinghouse"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA2_EA3239> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA2_EA3237> ;
    skos:definition "This class gives a specific behavior and responsibilities to the requests, depending of many factors and the source provided. It has a portabilityStatus as a specific attribute and a generalization to an existing entity called LogicalResourceRole. This entity helps with the management and tracking of the status for the portability requests, since it can be initiated, started, completed, among others. This track is made for the requests through the continuous communications with other sources, like the entities Number Portability Clearinghouse and External System as party roles. Therefore, NumberPortability, because of its complexity, its management of different states between its flow with other sources, works with a NumberPortabilityRole through an aggregation. All the number portability requests have a behavior with an affinity and dependency to the different parties created and added. (NP Clearinghouse, External System, Customer). This relation affects directly to the tracking for the portability through a status. For this we've created the specific attribute \"portabilityStatus\" for the entity \"NumberPortabilityRole\". Example:<br/><br/>PartyRole (<br/><br/>Customer:<br/><br/>NumberPortabilityRole (<br/><br/>portabilityStatus : created<br/><br/>)<br/><br/>NumberPortabilityClearinghouse:<br/><br/>NumberPortabilityRole (<br/><br/>portabilityStatus : accepted<br/><br/>)<br/><br/>)<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA2_EA3239" ;
    skos:prefLabel "NumberPortabilityRole"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3206> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3220> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3206" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure RO.01 - Resource Order Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3208> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3220> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3208" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure RO.02 - Relationships Inherited From Business Interaction"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3210> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3220> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3210" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure RO.03 - Relationships Inherited From BI Item"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3212> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3220> ;
    skos:definition "The NumberPortabilityPolicyRule entity describes business rules and regulatory policies; therefore, they exist before any request for number portability. Because of their need for conditions, events and particular actions to make, it inherits directly from PolicyRule and so, is an entity of great importance.<br/>The policies’ approach is to only be applied and be considered for the number portability itself, depending of the type of the request based on the BusinessInteractionType. They are a very important key when one is referring to number portability, since they are way too different for each country. In some are complex, in others simpler, and each one of them implement these policies in a different manner.<br/>As it seems in the figure, the new entity related to number portability is called NumberPortabilityPolicyRule and inherits from PolicyRule (from Policy ABE). These entities, like PolicyRule, PolicyRuleSpec, PolicyRuleBase, PolicyCondition, PolicyAction and PolicyEventBase are existing entities with all the behavior and elements shared with the new entity.<br/>In summary, NumberPortabilityPolicyRule is a key entity and a sub-class of PolicyRule in order to obtain the conditions, events and actions, which help especially for the penalty fees when certain conditions don't apply.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3212" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure RO.05 - Resource Number - Number Portability Policy"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3214> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3220> ;
    skos:definition "The Resource Number Portability Role ABE contains the entity NumberPortabilityRole and the entities needed to complete the roles associated, like the clearinghouse, which is strongly related with the number portability.<br/>NumberPortabilityRole is a class that gives a specific behavior and responsibilities to the requests, depending of many factors and the source provided. It has a portabilityStatus as a specific attribute and a generalization to an existing entity called LogicalResourceRole. This entity helps with the management and tracking of the status for the portability requests, since it can be initiated, started, completed, among others. This track is made for the requests through the continuous communications with other sources, like the entity NumberPortabilityClearinghouse as a party role, since the service providers don’t communicate directly for the number portability, and use the NumberPortabilityClearinghouse as an intermediary. Therefore, NumberPortability, because of its complexity, its management of different states between its flows with other sources, works with a NumberPortabilityRole through an aggregation. <br/>All the number portability requests have a behavior with and affinity and dependency to the different parties created and added. (Number Portability Clearinghouse, Service Provider, Customer). This relation affects directly to the tracking for the portability through a status (portabilityStatus attribute).<br/>In this figure it shows the relation of PartyRole (from Party ABE) with Party (Also from Party ABE) and how it relates with the role for number portability. For instance, there is a new subclass for PartyRole in order to reach every party who participates in the process. This new entity is NumberPortabilityClearinghouse, a very relevant party when a number portability is involved. <br/>On the side for the roles, the new entity is called NumberPortabilityRole, with an aggregation of many to 0.1 with the NumberPortabilityRequest. This role entity inherits form LogicalResourceRole (from Logical Role ABE), who inherits from the main parent, ResourceRole (from Resource ABE). This last entity is the one who has the association with PartyRole, through this, the whole communication flows perfectly.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3214" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure RO.06 - Resource Number - Number Portability Roles"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3216> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3220> ;
    skos:definition "The development of the model for the portability uses all the ABEs previously described and how each one of them relates to the other. There is an inheritance for the main entity NumberPortabililityRequest to see the subdivision more clearly. This entity has four types of requests for the number portability, NumberPortInRequest, NumberPortOutRequest, NumberPortOverRequest and NumberRetirementRequest. This main concrete class, NumberPortabilityRequest, has an aggregation for all the portability roles applied during the process. NumberPortabilityRole inherits all the behavior and attributes of LogicalResourceRole and relates to existing and new parties.<br/>NumberPortabilityRequest also forms a relation of many-to-many with the rules, with an association class in the middle called PortabilityRequestPolicyRule for the information in common.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3216" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure RO.06a - Resource Number Portability Relationships (OLD RO.04)"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3218> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3220> ;
    skos:definition "Another part to have in consideration is that NumberPortabilityRequest is a sub-class of the existing ResourceOrder. This entity is a sub-class itself of Request, which is a sub-class of BusinessInteraction. This last entity forms an aggregation with the BusinessInteractionItem creating the flow for the order of the requests entries for number portability, recognizing it through the attribute BusinessInteractionType. The following image shows this communication:<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3218" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure RO.07 - Resource Number Portability into Resource Order Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3221> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3220> ;
    skos:definition "A type of Request that represents a Serivce Order's services decomposed into the resources on which the services will be provisioned.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3221" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ResourceOrder"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3222> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3220> ;
    skos:definition "The purpose for the ResourceOrder expressed in terms of a ResourceSpecification or a Resource.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA5_EA3222" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ResourceOrderItem"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA1_EA3248> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA1_EA3250> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are the business entities aggregated under the <b>Resource Usage Entity </b>Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA1_EA3248" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure RUE.01 - Resource Usage Entity ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA1_EA3251> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA1_EA3250> ;
    skos:definition "An occurrence of employing a Resource for its intended purpose.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA1_EA3251" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ResourceUsage"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA2_EA3252> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA2_EA3254> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Following are the business entities aggregated under the <b>Resource Usage Specification </b>Aggregate Business Entity.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA2_EA3252" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure RUS.01 - Resource Usage Specification ABE Related Entities"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA2_EA3255> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA2_EA3254> ;
    skos:definition "A detailed description of a resource usage event (for example, a purchase or a lease of a resource).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA2_EA3255" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ResourceUsageSpecification"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3240> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3242> ;
    skos:definition "A resource usage represents any usage of resources in its broadest meaning, for example a usage of a product realized by a resource. <br/>A service usage represents any usage of service in its broadest meaning, for example or a usage of a service that realizes a product. <br/>A Product is realized as one or more Service(s) and/or Resource(s). A Product is created by instantiating a ProductOfferingSpecification and adding it to a specific customer account. In order to charge a service (or a resource) usage, the service (or resource) has to be associated to a product. <br/>The product usage describes the usage of an instantiated Product.<br/>Theoretically there are many different ways to model resource, service and product usage. For example:<br/> • As classes that inherited from Usage class.<br/> • As different states of the same Usage class.<br/>The following Figure describes the first approach where ResourceUsage, ServiceUsage and ProductUsage and its relationships with the specification.<br/><i>Refer to Common Domain guide book section Usage ABE for more details</i>.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3240" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure U.07 - Resource/Service/Product Usage - as classes that inherited from Usage class."@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3243> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3242> ;
    skos:definition "change derived relationship to direct relationship<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3243" ;
    skos:prefLabel "EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3243"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3244> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3242> ;
    skos:definition "change derived relationship to direct relationship<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3244" ;
    skos:prefLabel "EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3244"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3245> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3242> ;
    skos:definition "change derived relationship to direct relationship<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3245" ;
    skos:prefLabel "EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA6_EA3245"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA7_EA3256> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA7_EA3258> ;
    skos:definition "The following Figure shows one way to support tests for Product, Services, and Resources by applying the Entity/EntityRole pattern. This allows the same “Test Specification” to be used for many “Product TestSpecifications”, “ServiceTestSpecifications”, and “Resource TestSpecifications”. <br/>Product, Service, and Resource Tests are defined to be generalizations of the abstract “Test” class. In this way, the “Test” model may be used for the specification of all three types of tests. Each test, such as “ServiceTest” is associated to its relative entity under test, which in this case is “Service”. The relationships therefore between products, services, and resources, are maintained to the associated tests. As an example, a service test measure such as “Frame Loss Ratio” may translate to resource test measures “Number of frames sent” and “Number of frames received”. The metric “Number of Frames Lost” is derived from the resource test measures, and the “Frame Loss Ratio” is further calculated by dividing the number of frames lost by the number of frames sent.<br/><i>Refer to Common Domain guide book section Test ABE for more details</i><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA7_EA3256" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure T.04 - Product, Service and Resource Test Entities (Copy from Common)"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA7_EA3259> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA7_EA3258> ;
    skos:definition "An entity that exists for a controlled test invocation on a resource. The resource test is executed according to a schedule. and contains resource test configuration parameters that are to be applied at execution time, and resource test measures that result.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA7_EA3259" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ResourceTest"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA7_EA3260> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA7_EA3258> ;
    skos:definition "The resource test specification describes the resource test in terms of parameters to be configured and measures to be taken.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA7_EA3260" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ResourceTestSpec"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA8_EA3261> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA8_EA3263> ;
    skos:definition "The following Figure shows the associations that performance entities have with existing service and resource entities, as well as the association that the Performance entity has with the Customer entity. <br/><i>Note that the dark-shaded entities, CustomerFacingServiceSpecification and CustomerFacingService are not within the scope of the model as they related the Service domain with the Product domain, which is out of scope at this point in time. Also note that the ResouceSpecification is related directly to the PerformanceSpecification entity and Resource is related to the Performance entity, since both Service and Resource performance deal with Resources.</i><br/><br/>The Service Performance ABE collects, correlates, consolidates, and validates various performance statistics and other operational characteristics of customer and resource facing service entities. It provides a set of entities that can monitor and report on performance. Each of these entities also conducts network performance assessment against planned goals, performs various aspects of trend analysis, including error rate and cause analysis and Service degradation. Entities in this ABE also manage the traffic generated by a Service, as well as traffic trend analysis. This is important for newer technologies that separate data, control and management functions for a given Service.<br/><br/>The Resource Performance ABE collects, correlates, consolidates, and validates various performance statistics and other operational characteristics of Resource entities. It provides a set of entities that can monitor and report on performance. The entities in this ABE provide physical, logical, and performance information. Each of these entities also conducts network performance assessment against planned goals, performs various aspects of trend analysis, including error rate and cause analysis and Resource degradation. Entities in this ABE also manage traffic in a Resource. This includes statistics defining Resource loading, and traffic trend analysis.<br/><br/>The associations with the specification entities provide part of the definition of the performance specification entities. For example, the specification of a GGSN and SGSN define the types of network elements whose performance is measured. <br/>The cardinality of the association between ResourceSpecification and PerformanceSpecification is 0,2 because at most two types of resources’ performance is defined by a PerformanceSpecification. Similarly, the association between Resource and Performance also has a cardinality of 0,2. These Resource domain entities are directly related to the respective Performance ABE entities and not to ResourcePerformanceSpec and ResourcePerformance. The reason is that Resources are used to measure both Service-related and Resource-related performance.<br/>For the ServiceSpecification entity the cardinality is 1 because a given instance of a ServicePerformanceSpec entity measures the performance of a single ServiceSpecification entity, such as a mobile voice call. Similarly, the cardinality of the association between a Service and a Service performance is 1.<br/>The cardinality between a Customer and Performance is 0,1 because an instance of Performance may or may not be a measure of performance for an instance of Customer.<br/><i>Refer to Common Domain guide book section Performance ABE for more details</i><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA8_EA3261" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure PF.02 - Service, Resource, and Performance"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA8_EA3264> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA8_EA3263> ;
    skos:definition "A measure of the manner in which a Resource is functioning.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA8_EA3264" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ResourcePerformance"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA8_EA3265> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA8_EA3263> ;
    skos:definition "The invariant characteristics of a measure of the manner in which a Resource is functioning. Each related Performance instance will have the same invariant characteristics. However, the values associated with other characteristics of the instantiated Performance entity are specific to each instance.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA8_EA3265" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ResourcePerformanceSpec"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3266> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "A StockItem represents items used by Supply Chain for Stock and Shipping Management.<br/>The codeModel specifies the type of codification used for the stockItemCode.<br/>Two main types exist: EAN (European Article Numbering) or GTIN (Global Trade Item Numbering). A GTIN consists of a GS1 Company Prefix, an Item Reference Number and a Check Digit. <br/>Each of them is further defined by the length of the number such as EAN 13, GTIN-12 (USA / Canada for individual products), GTIN-13 (Rest of World for Individual products) and GTIN-14 (Worldwide for Product groupings).<br/>A ProductConfigSpec corresponds to a configuration of the related ProductSpecification. Ex: A Red Iphone with 128 GB memory. A GoodsProductSpec is realized by a unique StockItem according to the ProductConfigSpec.<br/>A StockItem might be realized by several ResourceSpecifications when different manufacturers produce the same StockItem (same characteristics and behaviour).<br/><i>A GoodsProductSpec might be created but it can’t be modified! I.e. only Create and Return operations are available for a GoodsProductSpec. For example, if the disk space of a TV decoder’s record capacity can be enhanced (realized through Software update), then we create a specific ProductSpecification for the Record Capacity.</i><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3266" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.01 - StockItem and other domains overview"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3268> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Let’s consider an Iphone that might be Red, Blue or Black.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">There will be as many StockItem as colors that exist.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Then the marketing might decide to propose </font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">Iphone Red, Blue or Black for Mass Market and for B2B in the context of a contract</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">And Iphone only Blue or Black for stand-alone offer</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">Different GoodsProductSpecs might exist concerning the same type of GoodsProduct.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The same ProductSpecification might correspond to many StockItems according to the configuration chosen.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The same StockItem might correspond to many ProductSpecifications.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3268" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.01-I01 - Same StockItem for different GoodsProductSpecs"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3270> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">This example illustrates the use case where two different manufacturers produce the same StockItem.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">This is the Supply Chain that is in charge of choosing between the two solutions.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">For example, the choice criteria might be based on price proposed by the supplier.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3270" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.01-I02 - StockItem & ResSpec illustration"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3272> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">A GoodsProduct might be either Rented or Sold.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\"><i>A Rented and a Sold GoodsProduct won’t have the same After-Sale Service</i></font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\"><i>Each GoodsProduct might be either in original or reconditioned condition</i></font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">If we want to sell the GoodsProduct in original or reconditioned condition two options exist. </font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">Define a unique ProductSpec with a characteristic proposing “original condition” or “reconditioned condition”</font></li></ul><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">Define two ProductSpecs, one for “original condition” and one for “reconditioned condition”</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\"><i>In this illustration we have chosen to define only one ProductSpec</i></font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Each ProductSpec might be sold by several ProductOfferings and with specific configuration restrictions.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">For Rented Livebox, it’s always the same StockItem.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Each Resource corresponding to this StockItem might be either NEW or reconditioned. It has no impact.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">For Sold Livebox, it won’t be the same StockItem according to its condition.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3272" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.01-I03 - StockItem Reconditioned"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3274> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "A StockItem is further defined by characteristics and characteristics values.<br/>A StockItem might have several values for the same Characteristic, but only if there is a default Value (the value of the “pre-configured” StockItem corresponding to factory configuration). This configuration can only be modified for the ProductSpec by a ProductSpec applying on it.<br/>For example, the disk space of a TV decoder’s record capacity can be enhanced (realized through Software update), then we create a specific ProductSpecification for the Record Capacity applying on the TV decoder ProductSpec.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3274" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.01a - StockItem detailed view"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3276> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">An Iphone might be Red, Blue or Black.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The Color is a Characteristic that might have more values than the ones available for an Iphone as it might be reused by several StokItems.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">A value might be contained by no StockItem.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3276" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.01a-I01 - StockItem Characteristics simple"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3278> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">An Iphone may exist with different Colors and different Memories.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The Iphone Black exist with 64Gb, 128Gb or 256Gb Memory.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The Iphone Red only exist with 64Gb or 128Gb Memory.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3278" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.01a-I02 - StockItem Characteristics complex"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3280> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\"><i>Rule Reminder: A GoodsProduct can be created or removed but it can’t be modified.</i></font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">So, if the customer wants more Recording Disk Space (change manufacturing configuration) he needs another ProductSpecification “Additional Space” that will apply on the GoodsProduct and that will update the Recording Disk Space thanks to a Software update.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">When the Decoder is provided to the Customer, it’s always configured with the default value</font>.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3280" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.01a-I03 - StockItem Characteristic default value"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3282> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">The TV Decoder is always provided with a configuration of 240 Gb and it can’t be modified by the Customer Order.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The corresponding ProductSpecification may propose only a sub-set of possible values and the OfferSpecification might be related to Tariffs according to the configuration.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">To increase the TV Decoder Space Disk, we use the “Additional Space Disk” Know-How.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3282" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.01a-I04 - TV decoder additional space"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3284> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "In the context of a ProductConfigurationSpec used for identifying a StockItem, it specifies a unique value for each configurable characteristic of the ProductSpecification.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3284" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.01b - StockItem and ProductConfigurationSpec"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3286> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Based on ProductSpecification characteristics and their values we can identify the different possible configurations. </font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">In this example the Iphone R/Bk/B GoodsProductSpec might be Red, Black or Blue.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">ProductConfigurationSpec of GoodsProductSpec might exist before StockItem identification but it can be in “Available” status only if the StockItem is identified and “Available”.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Then we can find the corresponding StockItem of each configuration.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3286" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.01b-I01 - Simple ProductConfigurationSpec"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3288> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">A GoodsProductSpec might have several configurable characteristics with several possible values for each.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">To declare ProductConfigurationSpec related to a ProductSpecification, each ProductSpecCharValue triggers the creation of a ProductConfSpecCharValue.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">One of the combination of characteristics’ values is Red & 64Gb.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Another combination of characteristics’ values is Red & 128Gb.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">3 other combinations of characteristics’ values exist with Black value.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">No ProductConfigurationSpec exist for Red Color and 256Gb as these values are incompatible.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3288" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.01b-I02 - Complex ProductConfigurationSpec"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3290> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "StockLocation represents places where StockItems might be stored.<br/>A StockLocation may involve several PartyRoles (owner of the StockLocation, operator of the StockLocation, user of the StockLocation...). A PartyRole may be involved in several StockLocation.<br/>A StockItemStockLevel represents the Stock Level of a StockItem stored in a StockLocation and available for SalesChannels.<br/>A StockItemStockLevel might be:<br/> • Available for sale to customers limited to SalesChannels<br/> • Available for use to build the Network or to provide furniture to employees<br/> • Returned: StockItems received back from the Customer that must be checked before being available such as rented material returned<br/> • Damaged: StockItems identified as damaged during a reception from a supplier or returned as damaged by a Customer or Employee<br/><i>Note: attributes starting with a slash (“/”) correspond to the result of a calculation. For example, /bookedQuantity is calculated adding all quantity booked and /quantity is calculated adding 1 for each Resource related to the StockItemStockLevel.</i><br/>A StockItemStockLevel if the quantity is non-zero is always composed of Resources.<br/>A Resource might have a serialNumber. Today in SID, only PhysicalResource, Equipment (sub-class of PhysicalResource) and InstalledSoftware (sub-class of LogicalResource) may have a serialNumber.<br/>Proposal: move serialNumber attribute at Resource Business Entity as a CompoundResource may also need a serialNumber.<br/>Booking or Replenishment requests might be formulated concerning a StockItemStockLevel:<br/> • Booking request: a booking request might come from a CustomerProductOrder in progress or simply from a salesperson that plan to place a huge quantity to a Customer. It carries a valid period to avoid freezing the stock.<br/> • Replenishment: a replenishment request is triggered when the quantity is under the reorderLevel. The status is “In progress” and the end date (from validPeriod) is specified when a corresponding purchase or movement from one StockLocation to another has been triggered.<br/>These requests might be cancelled (for example if the Customer abort his order).<br/>A StockItemRequest might be “Received” if the corresponding StockItemShipment is completed and the content has not yet been checked.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3290" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.02 - Stock Level and Stock Location"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3292> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Let’s consider 2 places where could be located StockItems:</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">A Central Warehouse dedicated for online sales located in Paris</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">A local store in Lyon located in Lyon</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">The same StockItem might be available for Sale in different Places.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">In the Central Warehouse: 498 items available. Reorder request must be triggered under 500 items available. So in this context, a purchase must have already bene done with 1000 items requested.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">In a local store in Lyon: 92 items available. Reorder request must be triggered under 100 items available. So in this context, a purchase must have already been done with 200 items requested.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Other StockLevel might exist for the same StockItem in the different Location for different Channels and / or in a different Status such as Damaged.</font>c<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3292" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.02-I01 - StockLocation"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3294> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">A service provider has technicians that will go to the customer’s house to install something.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Let’s say it is a broadband product, or some entertainment product (Satellite TV / cable TV).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">In order to perform the install, the technicians have some equipment they must install (a set-top box, some cables, some plugs, maybe a specialized WIFI box, etc).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">In his van, he has some number of these items to be used for the installs for the day.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">These are stock items with stock levels, and located in a Van (StockLocation). Some countries call this “boot” stock, because it is in the boot or trunk of the vehicle.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3294" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.02-I01a - StockLocation in a Van"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3296> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">The same StockItem might be available in different StockLocations for different SalesChannel.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">In this example, Iphone Red StockItem is available:</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">In the Central Warehouse for online or Store SalesChannels</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">And in Lyon Store only for Store SalesChannel</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">Many StockItems might be available in different StockLocations for different SalesChannels.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">In this example, in Lyon store you can find Iphone Red, Blue or Black.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">In addition, you also can have Iphone Red in Damaged status.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3296" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.02-I02 - StockLocation & SalesChannel"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3298> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">The same StockItem might be available in different status in different StockLocations.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Each Stock Level with a non-zero quantity either in “Available for sale”, “Available for use”, “Returned” or “Damaged” status contains Resources. Each of them might be related to a ResourceSpecification.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3298" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.02-I03 - StockLocations"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3300> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Let’s consider Iphone Red and Black under reorder level in Lyon store.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Two StockItemRequests would be created for Iphone Red and Black.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3300" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.02-I04 - StockLocation and StockItemRequest"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3302> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Let’s consider an Iphone Black StockItem available in Lyon store.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">And a Customer starting an order for an Iphone Black in Lyon store.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">According to Business rules, it might be possible to book one StockItem from the Stock level to make sure you can provide the Iphone Black if the order is validated.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">According to Business rules, the booking request will be valid only for a period of time.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">If the valid period is ended or the order cancelled, the booking request will be “Cancelled”.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3302" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.02-I05 - StockLocation and StockItemRequest for Booking"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3304> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Let’s consider a Livebox Rented with its related StockItem and ResourceSpecification </font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3304" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.02-I06a StockLocation and Resources"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3306> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Originally this StockItem might exist “Available for sale” in a StockLocation.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The StockItemStockLevel is related to the corresponding Resources.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Note: Only one instance of Resource presented here instead of 498.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3306" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.02-I06b StockLocation and Resources"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3308> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">When John Smith orders a Rented Livebox, the corresponding Offer and Product are created.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Once the Resource is destocked and assigned to John Smith Product, the StockItemStockLevel is debited and the Resource is assigned to John Smith Product</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3308" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.02-I06c StockLocation and Resources"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3310> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">When John Smith terminates his Rented Livebox Offer and gives back the Resource, the Resource is assigned to the Returned StockItemStockLevel.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3310" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.02-I06d StockLocation and Resources"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3312> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Then it will be analysed and either it will be assigned to Damaged or Available for sale stock level.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">In this illustration, it is moved to the Damaged Stock Level.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3312" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.02-I06e StockLocation and Resources"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3314> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "A StockItemShipment represents the order of Shipping received by the Supply Chain.<br/>A StockItemShipment might be triggered by a CustomerProductOrderItem of a ShippingProductSpec.<br/>Several StockItemShipments might be requested for example if all GoodsProductSpec are not available in the same StockLocation.<br/>Information coming from the ShippingProductSpec configuration are described at StockItemShipping level (to location, shipping delay…).<br/>A StockItemShipment might be triggered by one or many StockItemRequest. <br/>In this case information will come from the StockItemRequest(s).<br/>A StockItemShipment might be triggered by one or many StockItemRequest or exclusively by a CustomerProductOrderItem.<br/><i>The Supply Chain is in charge of optimizing the Shipments.</i><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3314" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.03 - StockItemShipment overview"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3316> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "A StockItemShipment is composed of items (StockItemShipmentItem) in charge of shipping one type of StockItem.<br/>A StockItemShipment requests the delivery of one or many StockItems <br/>Shipment from a StockLocation to another,<br/>Shipment from a StockLocation to a place (customer’s home or a Pick Up & Go place),<br/>By-hand delivery from a StockLocation in a Store.<br/>The actionRequested specifies the action requested such as Realize or Cancel.<br/>The shipmentType specifies the type of shipment such as Shipment or By-hand delivery.<br/>A StockItemShipment triggered by a CustomerProductOrder will move StockItems either to a StockLocation (Ex: if the Customer will pick up in a Store) or to a place (Ex: at customer’s home or a Pick Up & Go place)<br/>A StockItemShipment triggered by a StrockItemRequest will move StockItems to a StockLocation as the aim of the request is a StockItemLevel replenishment.<br/>A StockItemShipment always move StockItems from a StockLocation.<br/>Information used to build the StockItemShipmentItem comes either from the CustomerProductOrderItem of GoodsProductSpec or from the StockItemRequest<br/>The StockItemShipmentItem Specifies the StockItemLevel from which the StockItem(s) will be picked-up and possibly the StockItemLevel that will collect them.<br/>The StockItemShipment might be reported to a PartyRole. Usually if the StockItemShipment is related to ProductOrderItems then it’s the customer that will be contacted for follow-up, but if it corresponds to a by-hand delivery to the Customer realized by the technician in charge of installation, it’s the technician that will receive the follow-up to be able to pick-up the goods products.<br/>When StockItemShipment corresponds to replenishment request the follow-up will be received by the Employee in charge of the StockLocation replenishment follow-up.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3316" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.04 - StockItemShipment detailed view"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3318> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">In the same CustomerProductOrder a Customer has requested an Iphone Red and a Box to be shipped at home with the same shipment conditions.</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\"><i>All CustomerProductOrderItems are not shown here to simplify the illustration.</i></font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">The shipment CustomerProductOrderItem specifies the ContactAddress where GoodsProducts have to be shipped.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">A StockItemShipment is created and specifies the Place and configuration of the shipment such as the delivery type “At Home”.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">A StockItemShipmentItem is created for each CustomerProductOrderItems for GoodsProducts (i.e. one for the Iphone Red and one for the Box).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Each StockItemShipmentItem specifies the StockItem requested according to the GoodsProductSpec configuration carried by the CustomerProductOrderItem.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3318" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.04-I01 - StockItemShipment and CustomerProductOrder"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3320> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">A CustomerProductOrder might be placed with a Store. In this case, the ShippingProductSpec might be configured as “by-hand” at the StockLocation Place.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">A StockItemShipment is created with the deliveryType “by-hand” and specifying “Lyon store” as the StockLocation to be destocked.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Each GoodsProduct CustomerProductOrderItem will trigger a StockItemShipmentItem.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3320" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.04-I02 - Stock Item Shipment: by-hand delivery in a Store"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3322> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Lets’ consider “Lyon store” StockLocation where both Iphone Red and Black are under reorder Level.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">A Replenishment StockItemRequest will be triggered for each of them.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">If both StockItems to be shipped to the same location are available in the same StockLocation, it will be possible to identify a unique Shipment.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3322" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.04-I03 - Stock Item Shipment: StockItemRequestReplenishment"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3324> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "The StockItemShipment specifies a Place or a StockLocation where it has to be delivered.<br/>The follow-up might be sent to a Customer or an Employee (movement from one StockLocation to another or when the technician brings the goods products when installing).<br/>The Supply Chain chooses a Carrier to realize the StockItemShipment.<br/>Once the carrier to realize the StockItemShipment is identified, the ShipmentTracking is created according to information given by the Carrier such as its internal ID and the tracking URL that will be given to the Customer.<br/>Then we may interact with the Customer with this information<br/>Shipment might be done with several movements. For example the Shipment must be done from place A to place C, the first step might be to move from place A to Place B and the second one from Place B to place C.<br/>So one ShipmentCheckPoint is created for each step.<br/>Each time we may want to interact with the Customer to give him information about shipment progress and / or make an Appointment.<br/>When the parcel has been well received, the Carrier informs possibly the CSP with a proof of receipt and the status of the shipmentTracking might be changed to “completed”.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3324" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.05 - Shipment Tracking"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3326> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Let’s take the example of 2 Shipments that have to be realized. One from the Central Warehouse StockLocation located in Paris and the other from Lyon Store located in Lyon.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Once the Carrier is chosen, the ShipmentTracking will be created and the Carrier information collected.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The Carrier may send us information about a check point and we track this information.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The Carrier may send us information about a check point only when it is achieved or in advance with the expected date.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3326" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.05-I01 - Shipment Tracking"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3328> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Initially the shipment has to be done at Customer’s home.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">If ever the customer isn’t at home, the business rule might be to deliver the parcel in the nearby Pick-Up & Go. The status of the ShipmentCheckPoint (ST 02 Step 2) is changed to “aborted Customer not at home”.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Then a new ShipmentCheckPoint is created (ST 03 Step 3) specifying that the parcel will be delivered in the nearby Pick-Up & Go.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Once it is done, a new ShipmentCheckPoint is initialized specifying the parcel is available.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Once the parcel is picked-up by the customer, the CheckPoint is completed and the electronic or paper signature is tracked as a Document.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3328" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure SI.05-I02 - Shipment Tracking with issue"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3331> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3330> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3331" ;
    skos:prefLabel "EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA7_EA9_EA3331"@en .

