<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA4_EA3535> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA4_EA3537> ;
    skos:definition "An Account specifies basic attributes and relationships that describe an account.<br/>An Account aims to register all Credits and Debits according to criteria. It carries one or many Balances (results of Credits and Debits) and might use one or many Currencies.<br/>Each Account is possessed by one or many PartyRoles such as the Holder or the Payer of a CustomerBillingAccount.<br/>Each Account might be related to other Accounts such as a parent / child relationship.<br/>BusinessPartnerAccount, CustomerBillingAccount and FinancialAccount are types of Account.<br/>A BusinessPartnerAccount and CustomerBillingAccount carries additional information (such as creditLimit) and have specific relationships.<br/>A FinancialAccount is part of the sub-ledger accounting that aggregates the amounts of one or more business partner and / or Customer accounts owned by a given party. It’s an internal view of the CSP to manage incomes and outcomes.<br/>Each accounting event from a BusinessPartnerAccount or CustomerBillingAccount is logged to a FinancialAccount according to the assignment rules specified by BsuinessPartnerAccountAssignment and CustomerBillingAccountAssignment.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA4_EA3535" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Acc.01 - Account Overview (copy from Common)"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA4_EA3538> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA4_EA3537> ;
    skos:definition "A BusinessPartnerAccount is an arrangement that a Party has with an enterprise (such as a communication service provider) through which the enterprise collects AppliedPartyBillingRate (i.e. charges) to structure bills. It also collects payments for ProductOfferings that are supplied by the enterprise to the Party. The AppliedPartyBillingRates are invoiced to the BusinessPartnerAccount via PartyBills.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA4_EA3538" ;
    skos:prefLabel "BusinessPartnerAccount"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA4_EA3539> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA4_EA3537> ;
    skos:definition "The BusinessPartnerAccountAssignment specifies rules for a BusinessPartnerAccount on how assignment to a FinancialAccount has to be done for each accounting event.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA4_EA3539" ;
    skos:prefLabel "BusinessPartnerAccountAssignment"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA4_EA3540> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA4_EA3537> ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA4_EA3540" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure Acc.01 - Account Overview"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3544> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3554> ;
    skos:definition "Party Settlement ABE deals with an enterprise’s settlements with other parties. A PartySettlement is a monetary value that will be paid to a party by the enterprise or a party will pay to the enterprise as a result of the usage/recurring fee of a product/service/resource provided. PartySettlement is managed by agreements and can be created between an enterprise and other MVNOs, dealers, retailers, content providers, etc. A service provider’s dealer earns commissions for handling customer business interactions such as new sale or upsell. A mobile service provider pays the settlement amount to its roaming partner when one of its customers connects the roaming partner’s line. A party can play a role of customer and a partner at the same time or it can be only a partner.<br/>As another example, Amazon offers a Thermo-Kitty Heated cat bed on behalf of other vendors.<br/>Two offers are proposed in this way by Amazon.<br/>The first offer is Quidsi’s offer for which Quidsi is the provider and has delegated several processes to Amazon (order handling, fulfillment, collecting payment..). The price for this offer is $44.79.<br/>The second offer is GlobalPets’ offer for which GlobalPets is the provider and has delegated only the order handling to Amazon. The price for this offer is $48.<br/>Amazon has different agreements with Quidsi and GlobalPets and will earn predefined settlement amount for selling each offer. <br/>Quidsi and GlobalPets can also be a customer of Amazon.<br/>For Party Settlements between Quidsi and Amazon or between GlobalPets and Amazon, the entity PartySettlement is calculated according to the rules, limits, amounts, and policies defined in the agreement drawn up between the enterprise and other parties.<br/>PartySettlementRole captures all the roles that are included like settlement payment responsible and for example, the role of parties responsible for a) calculating or b) forwarding settlements, etc.<br/>The following figure shows the PartySettlement Agreement model.<br/><i>Party Settlement ABE is still preliminary</i><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3544" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure P.31 - Party Settlement Agreement"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3546> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3554> ;
    skos:definition "PartySettlement is described by PartySettlementSpecification. A PartySettlementSpecification describes a pattern/category of similar Settlement Specifications. <br/>PartySettlementSpecVersion is a particular form or variety of a PartySettlementSpecification that is different from others or from the original. A version generally uses time as dimension to reflect changes between PartySettlementSpecVersions. The form represents differences in properties that characterize a PartySettlementSpecification, that are not enough to warrant creating a new PartySettlementSpecification.<br/>Additional information can be stored via Characteristics for PartySettlement and PartySettlementSpecification.<br/>PartySettlementSpecRelationship is a significant connection between two PartySettlementSpecifications such as migration, substitution, dependency, exclusivity.<br/>The following figure shows the PartySettlementSpecification model.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3546" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure P.32 - Party Settlement Specification"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3548> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3554> ;
    skos:definition "PartySettlement items are defined in AppliedPartyBillingRate. For example, if a dealer’s settlement is $10 in total. The item details of the settlement are in AppliedPartyBillingRate such as $5 for a sale order, $3 for an upsell order, and $2 for a customer support. So, the corresponding customer charge details are in AppliedCustomerBillingRate.<br/>PartySettlement is created for a PartyAccount.<br/>The following figure shows the PartySettlement AppliedBillingRate model.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3548" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure P.33 - Party Settlement Applied Billing Rate"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3550> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3554> ;
    skos:definition "PartySettlement is paid by PartySettlementPayment which links to a more general entity PartyPayment.<br/>PartyPayment is received from and made to PartyRoles.<br/>The following figure shows the PartySettlement Payment model.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3550" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure P.34 - Party Settlement Payment"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3552> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3554> ;
    skos:definition "The following figure shows the whole PartySettlement model.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3552" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure P.35 - Party Settlement Full Diagram"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3555> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3554> ;
    skos:definition "A monetary value that will be paid to a party by the enterprise or a party will pay to the enterprise as a result of the usage/recurring fee of a product/service/resource provided. PartySettlement is managed by agreements and can be created between an enterprise and other MVNOs, dealers, retailers, content providers, etc.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3555" ;
    skos:prefLabel "PartySettlement"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3556> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3554> ;
    skos:definition "A PartyPayment applied to a PartySettlement.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3556" ;
    skos:prefLabel "PartySettlementPayment"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3557> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3554> ;
    skos:definition "A significant connection between two PartySettlements such as migration, substitution, dependency, exclusivity.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3557" ;
    skos:prefLabel "PartySettlementRelationship"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3558> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3554> ;
    skos:definition "PartySettlementRole captures all the roles that are included like settlement payment responsible and for example, the role of parties responsible for a) calculating or b) forwarding settlements, etc.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3558" ;
    skos:prefLabel "PartySettlementRole"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3559> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3554> ;
    skos:definition "A detailed description of PartySettlement.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3559" ;
    skos:prefLabel "PartySettlementSpecification"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3560> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3554> ;
    skos:definition "A significant connection between two PartySettlementSpecifications such as migration, substitution, dependency, exclusivity.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3560" ;
    skos:prefLabel "PartySettlementSpecRelationship"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3561> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3554> ;
    skos:definition "A particular form or variety of a PartySettlementSpecification that is different from others or from the original. The form represents differences in properties that characterize a PartySettlementSpecification, that are not enough to warrant creating a new PartySettlementSpecification.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA1_EA3561" ;
    skos:prefLabel "PartySettlementSpecVersion"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3583> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3603> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Let’s take the example of “The Enterprise” that buys ProductOfferingSpecification “PO1” to “Party 1”.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">“Party 1” is paid a fixed price “POP1” for each “PO1” whatever “The Enterprise” earns from its own Customers.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">As usual, an Agreement is approved between “The Enterprise” and “Party1”, but without the need of a Revenue Sharing Agreement.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3583" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Use case without any Revenue Sharing"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3585> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3603> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Let’s take the example of “The Enterprise” that buys ProductOfferingSpecification “PO1” to “Party 1”.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Enterprise pays a fixed price POP1 for PO1 to Party 1 for the right to use ProductSpecification PS1.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The Enterprise uses ProductSpecification PS1 to build the ProductSpecification PS2 and sells PS2 through its own ProductOfferingSpecification PO.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">And the revenue is shared (POP2a) based on what is paid by customers to the Enterprise (POP2). For example, Enterprise has to pay 10% from POP2.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3585" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Use case with Revenue Sharing based on Customer charges collected"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3587> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3603> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">The payment flow is like this</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3587" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Use case with Revenue Sharing Payment flow"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3589> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3603> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">In this case it would be illustrated this way in the model.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3589" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure PRS.07 – Illustration 01: Revenue Sharing based on Customer charges collected"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3591> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3603> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Enterprise sells on behalf of Party 1 but DOES NOT collect the money. The Payment from the customer is directly collected on Party 1’s Bank Account. Enterprise enables the customer to pay Party 1.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">This example is like ETSY.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Enterprise is paid through a Payment from Party 1 (POP2) according to the Product Offering Process delegation. The amount paid by Party 1 to the Enterprise for “selling on behalf” (process delegation) is calculated based on the ProductOfferingSpecification PO1 price (POP1).</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3591" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Use case with Revenue Sharing: Sell on behalf of"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3593> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3603> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Two options might exist for an agreement between the Enterprise and the Party</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">either the Party 1 shares the revenue with the Enterprise. In this case, Party 1 directly shares revenue with the Enterprise and they have a <b>Revenue Sharing Agreement</b>.</font></li></ul>2 sub-cases:<br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">according to degree of trust, they accept the payment from Party 1 without controlling</font></li><li><font color=\"#29313b\">or the Enterprise calculates to check what Party 1 owes producing a revenue sharing notice</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">or the Enterprise may charge some type of fees (listing or marketing) for selling on behalf of Party 1. In this case Party 1 receives an invoice from Enterprise and no Revenue Sharing Agreement is required (not illustrated here)</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3593" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Options"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3595> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3603> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">In this case it would be illustrated this way in the model.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3595" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure PRS.07 – Illustration 02: Sell on behalf of use case 1"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3597> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3603> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">Enterprise sells on behalf of Party 1 and COLLECTS the money on its Bank Account.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">An invoice netting is done between what is received by the Enterprise from the Customer (has to be paid back to Party1) and what Enterprise must receive for selling on behalf of Party1 and enabling the payment (POP2).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Note: eTOM has to be updated to support these requirements.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">The amount paid by Party 1 to the Enterprise for “selling on behalf” (process delegation) is a fixed amount (POP2) that doesn’t depend on the ProductOfferingSpecification sold (PO1 Price POP1).</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">This example is like Amazon.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3597" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Use case with Revenue Sharing: Sell on behalf of use case 2"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3599> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3603> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">The flow of payment is like this.</font><br/><font color=\"#29313b\">Sub-use cases might exist</font><br/><ul><li><font color=\"#29313b\">Party 1 sends an invoice to Enterprise and Enterprise pays Party 1 (not invoice netting)</font></li></ul><font color=\"#29313b\">Enterprise directly sends the payment to Party 1 (not invoice netting)</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3599" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Party Revenue SharingUC 2 The flow of payment"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3601> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/sid/sid_EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3603> ;
    skos:definition "<font color=\"#29313b\">In this case it would be illustrated this way in the model.</font><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:sid ;
    skos:notation "sid:EARoot_EA4_EA2_EA8_EA5_EA2_EA1_EA3601" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Figure PRS.07 – Illustration 02: Sell on behalf of use case 2"@en .

